2
00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:43.711
(SOFT TRADITIONAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

3
00:00:44.629 --> 00:00:47.215
WOMAN: (IN MANDARIN)
The legend of the ten rings

4
00:00:47.423 --> 00:00:50.092
has been told for thousands of years.

5
00:00:51.969 --> 00:00:56.432
Every generation.
the story grows.

6
00:00:56.599 --> 00:01:01.395
But at its centre
there is always one man.

7
00:01:05.316 --> 00:01:06.567
(HORSE GRUNTS)

8
00:01:10.112 --> 00:01:16.953
Some say he found the rings in a crater
or stole them from a tomb.

9
00:01:19.705 --> 00:01:22.541
They gave him the strength of a god.

10
00:01:22.708 --> 00:01:26.212
and the gift of eternal life.

11
00:01:29.757 --> 00:01:31.467
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

12
00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:36.389
He could have used them for good.

13
00:01:36.472 --> 00:01:37.974
(ARROWS WHIZZING)

14
00:01:40.810 --> 00:01:42.979
But all he wanted...

15
00:01:43.145 --> 00:01:44.855
was power.

16
00:01:45.398 --> 00:01:46.565
(RINGS CLANG)

17
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:48.901
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

18
00:01:48.985 --> 00:01:50.152
(ARROWS CLATTERING)

19
00:01:55.741 --> 00:01:57.618
(BLASTING)

20
00:01:57.702 --> 00:01:58.911
(SOLDIERS EXCLAIM)

21
00:01:58.995 --> 00:02:00.913
(ALL GRUNTING)

22
00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:09.255
(SOLDIER SCREAMS)

23
00:02:11.882 --> 00:02:13.301
(SOLDIERS GROANING)

24
00:02:17.555 --> 00:02:18.723
(CRASHING)

25
00:02:19.765 --> 00:02:21.267
(SOLDIERS YELLING)

26
00:02:22.893 --> 00:02:24.895
(SOLDIERS GRUNTING
SYNCHRONOUSLY)

27
00:02:26.939 --> 00:02:30.484
He called his army The Ten Rings.

28
00:02:32.695 --> 00:02:37.825
Over the centuries. they spread
into every corner of the world.

29
00:02:38.367 --> 00:02:39.785
(ALL GRUNTING)

30
00:02:45.166 --> 00:02:47.960
They moved in the shadows...

31
00:02:48.044 --> 00:02:49.170
(SCREAMING)

32
00:02:50.338 --> 00:02:52.381
Toppled governments...

33
00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:56.969
And changed the course of history.

34
00:02:57.053 --> 00:02:58.262
(MEN SCREAM)

35
00:03:13.194 --> 00:03:17.490
He chased money and power
for a thousand years.

36
00:03:18.324 --> 00:03:21.452
But he still wanted more.

37
00:03:26.791 --> 00:03:28.542
(IN MANDARIN)
Have you heard the legend of Ta Lo?

38
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:34.840
A hidden village with mythical creatures
and ancient magic.

39
00:03:35.007 --> 00:03:39.970
Where people practise
a martial arts style from the gods.

40
00:03:40.262 --> 00:03:42.014
I want to find it.

41
00:03:42.181 --> 00:03:45.643
Of course. I'll send a scout
to explore the area.

42
00:03:45.810 --> 00:03:48.437
and come back
with more information.

43
00:03:50.689 --> 00:03:52.566
I want to go now.

44
00:03:53.150 --> 00:03:54.860
(SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

45
00:04:16.173 --> 00:04:17.341
The forest...

46
00:04:19.301 --> 00:04:21.929
...is moving.

47
00:04:22.304 --> 00:04:23.681
(TREES RATTLING)

48
00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:28.269
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

49
00:04:30.187 --> 00:04:31.188
(GRUNTS)

50
00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:39.488
(CRASHING)

51
00:04:52.126 --> 00:04:55.838
WOMAN: He had nothing left
on Earth to conquer.

52
00:04:59.967 --> 00:05:04.472
That's when he came
for my home.

53
00:05:13.564 --> 00:05:15.816
Where's the entrance
to Ta Lo?

54
00:05:17.568 --> 00:05:19.862
You're not welcome
in our village.

55
00:05:21.447 --> 00:05:23.574
You don't know who
you're talking to.

56
00:05:24.158 --> 00:05:25.826
I don't care who you are.

57
00:05:26.535 --> 00:05:30.372
Turn around now.
and I won't have to hurt you.

58
00:05:37.755 --> 00:05:38.756
(SCOFFS)

59
00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:40.341
Is that all?

60
00:05:40.883 --> 00:05:43.093
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

61
00:05:48.432 --> 00:05:49.767
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

62
00:05:57.566 --> 00:05:58.567
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

63
00:06:01.654 --> 00:06:03.656
(TRADITIONAL MUSIC PLAYING)

64
00:06:15.251 --> 00:06:16.252
(GRUNTS)

65
00:06:21.382 --> 00:06:22.925
(BOTH GRUNTING)

66
00:06:48.659 --> 00:06:50.661
(TRADITIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES)

67
00:07:17.146 --> 00:07:18.147
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

68
00:07:20.608 --> 00:07:21.775
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

69
00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:27.031
(GRUNTS)

70
00:07:41.337 --> 00:07:43.297
(ENERGY WHIRRING)

71
00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:45.966
(GRUNTING)

72
00:07:52.306 --> 00:07:53.349
(GASPS)

73
00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:02.316
LI: That was the first time
I met your father.

74
00:08:04.318 --> 00:08:05.986
(SOFT TRADITIONAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

75
00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:09.823
He was the last person
I thought I'd fall for.

76
00:08:11.742 --> 00:08:14.578
But love had other plans.

77
00:08:18.248 --> 00:08:20.542
Shang-Chi.

78
00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:23.504
there's much more to know
about the legend of the rings.

79
00:08:23.671 --> 00:08:27.466
but you'll learn about that
when you're older.

80
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:33.347
If Dad's rings were so powerful.
how did you beat him?

81
00:08:35.057 --> 00:08:41.855
Where I'm from. we are empowered
by the magic of the Great Protector.

82
00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:49.196
When you have the heart
of our dragon.

83
00:08:49.363 --> 00:08:52.408
you can do some amazing things.

84
00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:55.869
Can you still do those things?

85
00:08:57.746 --> 00:09:01.959
I left those powers in Ta Lo
with our dragon.

86
00:09:02.126 --> 00:09:05.587
but what I got in return
is so much better.

87
00:09:05.671 --> 00:09:06.755
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

88
00:09:09.675 --> 00:09:11.844
I want you to have this.

89
00:09:13.637 --> 00:09:15.848
Whenever you feel lost.

90
00:09:16.014 --> 00:09:19.017
this will help you
find your way home.

91
00:09:19.810 --> 00:09:21.270
Can you remember that?

92
00:09:27.609 --> 00:09:28.777
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

93
00:09:29.236 --> 00:09:30.738
(ALARM BEEPING)

94
00:09:31.613 --> 00:09:32.823
(BEEPING STOPS)

95
00:09:36.410 --> 00:09:37.411
(SIGHS)

96
00:09:41.248 --> 00:09:42.458
(IN ENGLISH) Okay.

97
00:10:07.357 --> 00:10:09.651
- (HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)
- (PANTING)

98
00:10:25.793 --> 00:10:27.294
(ENGINE REVS)

99
00:10:32.007 --> 00:10:34.009
(HIP-HOP MUSIC CONTINUES)

100
00:10:44.603 --> 00:10:45.604
Hello. sir.

101
00:10:45.729 --> 00:10:48.065
- welcome to the Fairmont...
- (GASPING)

102
00:10:48.565 --> 00:10:49.566
I'm driving.

103
00:10:49.733 --> 00:10:51.193
No. you're not... Katy.

104
00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:53.237
Hey. hey. get back here.

105
00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:54.363
Give me the key.

106
00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:58.200
(SIGHS) Please open the door.

107
00:10:58.283 --> 00:11:00.828
- (ENGINE ROARS)
- Oh. my God.

108
00:11:01.119 --> 00:11:02.955
- Get out.
- You get in!

109
00:11:03.038 --> 00:11:04.081
Look. if happens
to this thing.

110
00:11:04.164 --> 00:11:05.165
we're gonna be jobless

111
00:11:05.332 --> 00:11:06.500
and in debt
for the rest of our lives.

112
00:11:06.667 --> 00:11:08.752
Oh. come on. Nothing's gonna
happen to this car.

113
00:11:08.919 --> 00:11:10.337
I'm the Asian Jeff Gordon.

114
00:11:10.504 --> 00:11:11.672
I don't know who that is.

115
00:11:11.839 --> 00:11:13.632
Most career wins
in all of NASCAR history?

116
00:11:13.799 --> 00:11:15.300
Please get out of the car.

117
00:11:15.759 --> 00:11:16.760
Shaun.

118
00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:18.971
we've been friends
for 10 years. okay?

119
00:11:19.137 --> 00:11:21.181
- You know I'm not an idiot.
- (SIGHS)

120
00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:24.393
Please. get in. I'll go slow.

121
00:11:24.601 --> 00:11:26.895
- (ENGINE REVVING)
- (HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

122
00:11:26.979 --> 00:11:28.689
- (GIGGLES)
- (GASPS) Katy. watch the...

123
00:11:30.607 --> 00:11:31.942
(TYRES SCREECHING)

124
00:11:35.404 --> 00:11:36.405
SHAUN: <i>I knew Katy was trouble</i>

125
00:11:36.488 --> 00:11:37.823
<i>the first day we met
in high school.</i>

126
00:11:38.031 --> 00:11:39.074
I was getting picked on a lot.

127
00:11:39.157 --> 00:11:41.076
for all the reasons
we all get picked on a lot.

128
00:11:41.577 --> 00:11:42.953
Plus. I had just moved
to the US.

129
00:11:43.036 --> 00:11:44.496
so I was struggling
with my English.

130
00:11:44.663 --> 00:11:45.747
and I was on my way
to lunch one day

131
00:11:45.831 --> 00:11:47.666
when this guy
who was like twice my size

132
00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:48.750
yells at me
from down the hall.

133
00:11:48.834 --> 00:11:50.127
"What's up. Gangnam Style?"

134
00:11:50.878 --> 00:11:52.754
So I yelled back.
"I'm not Korean. idiot."

135
00:11:52.838 --> 00:11:53.839
And I turn the corner.

136
00:11:53.922 --> 00:11:55.549
and I see this guy
drop his backpack.

137
00:11:55.716 --> 00:11:56.967
he's getting
all up in his face...

138
00:11:57.134 --> 00:11:58.927
And right before he was about
to throw the first punch.

139
00:11:59.094 --> 00:12:00.929
Katy comes out of nowhere.

140
00:12:01.096 --> 00:12:04.349
steps right between us
and starts screaming the lyrics

141
00:12:04.433 --> 00:12:05.851
to <i>Hotel California.</i>

142
00:12:06.018 --> 00:12:07.019
What?

143
00:12:07.185 --> 00:12:09.229
It's the art of confusion.
Works great on stupid people.

144
00:12:09.438 --> 00:12:10.480
SHAUN:And that's how we met.

145
00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:12.065
Then I pulled him
into the parking lot...

146
00:12:12.232 --> 00:12:13.358
At which point she revealed

147
00:12:13.442 --> 00:12:15.736
that she had also swiped
the keys to the guy's Mustang.

148
00:12:15.903 --> 00:12:17.988
Yeah. we went on a little
joyride around the block.

149
00:12:18.071 --> 00:12:19.531
And your wife
was in the car. too.

150
00:12:19.698 --> 00:12:21.325
- That's true. You were.
- What?

151
00:12:21.408 --> 00:12:22.826
I was just in the back seat.

152
00:12:22.910 --> 00:12:23.911
That's a part of the car.

153
00:12:23.994 --> 00:12:25.078
That's still
a part of the car.

154
00:12:25.162 --> 00:12:26.788
How have you
never told me this story?

155
00:12:26.955 --> 00:12:28.123
You know.
before she was a lawyer.

156
00:12:28.206 --> 00:12:29.458
your girl was pretty wild.

157
00:12:29.708 --> 00:12:31.293
Oh! What happened?

158
00:12:33.128 --> 00:12:34.296
I grew up.

159
00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:36.089
What's that supposed to mean?

160
00:12:36.173 --> 00:12:37.174
Yeah. what's that
supposed to mean?

161
00:12:37.257 --> 00:12:38.926
That maybe there's a point

162
00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:40.969
where you're supposed
to stop going on joyrides

163
00:12:41.136 --> 00:12:43.555
and start thinking about
living up to your potential.

164
00:12:43.722 --> 00:12:45.223
Please tell me
you're kidding. Soo.

165
00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:46.391
SOO: Look.

166
00:12:46.600 --> 00:12:47.643
we're now living in a world

167
00:12:47.726 --> 00:12:48.727
where at any moment

168
00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:50.562
half the population
can just disappear.

169
00:12:51.313 --> 00:12:53.565
Life's too short
and too fragile.

170
00:12:53.732 --> 00:12:55.317
Katy. you're a valet driver

171
00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:56.860
with an honours degree
from Berkeley.

172
00:12:57.027 --> 00:12:59.279
and Shaun can speak.
like. four languages.

173
00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:01.365
You've always been the most
talented people I know.

174
00:13:01.531 --> 00:13:03.617
I just don't get why
you're scared

175
00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:05.577
to actually use it
for something serious.

176
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:07.287
Wow.

177
00:13:08.163 --> 00:13:10.874
You sound like my mom.
You also...

178
00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:12.376
dress like her
a little bit. too.

179
00:13:12.459 --> 00:13:14.503
- Where's this from. Talbots?
- (SOO LAUGHS)

180
00:13:14.586 --> 00:13:16.505
We're not running
from adulthood.

181
00:13:16.672 --> 00:13:18.966
How is it running to have jobs
that you actually like?

182
00:13:19.132 --> 00:13:20.634
Yeah. that doesn't
even make any sense.

183
00:13:20.717 --> 00:13:23.095
(FUMBLES) Did you think
valet parking is easy?

184
00:13:23.261 --> 00:13:25.180
It's like the most
challenging job ever.

185
00:13:25.263 --> 00:13:27.516
You need people skills.
driving skills...

186
00:13:27.724 --> 00:13:29.226
KATY: Soo can't even
parallel park.

187
00:13:29.309 --> 00:13:30.352
(SHAUN LAUGHS)

188
00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:32.813
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

189
00:13:32.896 --> 00:13:35.565
Well. it's almost midnight.
We got the early shift.

190
00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:38.735
Should probably be
responsible. go to sleep.

191
00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:40.612
Yeah. we can be responsible.
We can do that.

192
00:13:40.779 --> 00:13:42.239
Or...

193
00:13:42.406 --> 00:13:46.118
BOTH: (SINGING) <i>Over.
sideways and under on a...</i>

194
00:13:46.284 --> 00:13:48.495
<i>Take my horse
to the old town road</i>

195
00:13:48.578 --> 00:13:49.579
<i>I'm gonna</i>

196
00:13:49.663 --> 00:13:51.790
<i>Close my eyes</i>

197
00:13:52.541 --> 00:13:53.625
<i>I don't wanna...</i>

198
00:13:53.834 --> 00:13:55.460
(MUFFLED MUSIC PLAYING)

199
00:13:55.544 --> 00:13:57.170
(BOTH SNORING SOFTLY)

200
00:14:01.383 --> 00:14:03.468
(INDIE POP MUSIC PLAYING)

201
00:14:27.534 --> 00:14:28.660
Morning. Mrs Chen.

202
00:14:28.827 --> 00:14:29.953
She's not ready yet.

203
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:31.788
Come have some joe
while you wait.

204
00:14:33.457 --> 00:14:35.417
Katy. Shaun's here.

205
00:14:35.584 --> 00:14:37.335
Yeah. Mom.
be there in a minute.

206
00:14:37.419 --> 00:14:38.420
Ruihua.

207
00:14:38.503 --> 00:14:41.006
you're supposed to be helping
your dad stock the shop.

208
00:14:41.173 --> 00:14:44.342
Mom. I can't work on an empty
stomach. my legs get crampy.

209
00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:45.886
Maybe Shaun can help him

210
00:14:45.969 --> 00:14:48.180
instead of just showing up
every day to eat our food.

211
00:14:48.346 --> 00:14:49.556
I'm happy to help.

212
00:14:49.723 --> 00:14:52.434
No. it's Ruihua's job.
let him do it.

213
00:14:53.101 --> 00:14:54.144
Waipo.

214
00:14:55.312 --> 00:14:56.938
(IN MANDARIN) That seat's for Waigong.

215
00:14:57.564 --> 00:14:59.107
(IN ENGLISH) Oh. sorry.

216
00:14:59.191 --> 00:15:04.613
He's getting all his favourite things
this year for the Day of the Dead.

217
00:15:04.780 --> 00:15:06.364
(IN ENGLISH) Are you sure
that Waigong's allowed to take

218
00:15:06.448 --> 00:15:07.449
Funyuns and cigarettes

219
00:15:07.532 --> 00:15:08.742
back to the afterlife?

220
00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:10.577
He can take anything.

221
00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:14.748
Last year I put a bottle of whisky
on his grave...

222
00:15:15.123 --> 00:15:16.833
And it was gone the next morning.

223
00:15:17.084 --> 00:15:18.085
(SHAUN CHUCKLES)

224
00:15:18.168 --> 00:15:21.421
I know you kids think it's silly.

225
00:15:21.505 --> 00:15:23.298
(IN ENGLISH) We don't think
it's silly. Waipo.

226
00:15:23.924 --> 00:15:25.967
We just know Waigong would've
wanted you to move on

227
00:15:26.051 --> 00:15:27.135
and enjoy your life.

228
00:15:27.219 --> 00:15:29.429
"Moving on"
is an American idea.

229
00:15:29.596 --> 00:15:31.765
You're American. Mom!
Don't forget.

230
00:15:32.349 --> 00:15:33.350
MRS CHEN: Shaun.

231
00:15:33.517 --> 00:15:36.686
did my daughter apply
to any new jobs this week?

232
00:15:36.853 --> 00:15:38.605
She really likes her job.

233
00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:39.856
We both do.

234
00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:40.941
KATY: Mm-hmm.

235
00:15:41.024 --> 00:15:42.818
Waigong didn't move here
from Hunan

236
00:15:42.984 --> 00:15:44.528
so you could park cars
for a living.

237
00:15:46.488 --> 00:15:47.572
Well. on that note.

238
00:15:47.656 --> 00:15:49.116
I think we're gonna
miss our bus.

239
00:15:49.199 --> 00:15:50.242
SHAUN: Mm.

240
00:15:50.325 --> 00:15:52.077
KATY: I'm sorry
for my unacceptable job.

241
00:15:52.244 --> 00:15:53.537
And for staying out late
last night.

242
00:15:53.620 --> 00:15:55.163
trying to enjoy my life.

243
00:15:55.622 --> 00:15:57.499
But one day. I'll make you
proud. I promise.

244
00:15:57.666 --> 00:15:59.042
I'm proud of you. sis.

245
00:15:59.209 --> 00:16:01.670
Parking cars is super hard.

246
00:16:01.878 --> 00:16:02.879
Thanks. bro.

247
00:16:02.963 --> 00:16:04.214
Maybe one day you'll pass
your driver's test.

248
00:16:04.297 --> 00:16:05.298
live the dream like me.

249
00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:06.466
Come on. Shaun. let's go.

250
00:16:06.758 --> 00:16:08.176
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)

251
00:16:08.260 --> 00:16:09.845
- (KISSES)
- (EXCLAIMS. SPEAKS MANDARIN)

252
00:16:09.928 --> 00:16:11.888
When are you two going
to get married?

253
00:16:11.972 --> 00:16:13.265
Waipo. we're just friends.

254
00:16:13.348 --> 00:16:14.349
(SCOFFS)

