Go. Wong!

511
00:30:56.313 --> 00:30:57.773
I always bet on Asian.

512
00:30:57.940 --> 00:30:59.400
Oh. my God.

513
00:30:59.567 --> 00:31:01.360
Yeah. look. I'm not
going up there. okay?

514
00:31:01.444 --> 00:31:02.778
- I'm just trying to...
- Whoa. whoa. whoa.

515
00:31:02.862 --> 00:31:03.904
It's too late to back out now.

516
00:31:03.988 --> 00:31:05.656
- You already committed. bro.
- SHANG-CHI: What?

517
00:31:05.740 --> 00:31:07.783
JON JON: You signed
the contract. remember?

518
00:31:07.950 --> 00:31:09.285
Your name's on the roster.

519
00:31:09.493 --> 00:31:11.203
The bets are piling in.

520
00:31:11.370 --> 00:31:13.414
- Really? What's our cut?
- Oh. it's huge.

521
00:31:13.581 --> 00:31:14.582
It doesn't matter.

522
00:31:14.749 --> 00:31:15.833
It matters.

523
00:31:16.459 --> 00:31:18.711
Dude. I saw you
fight five assassins

524
00:31:18.794 --> 00:31:20.755
and a giant Romanian
with a razor for an arm

525
00:31:20.921 --> 00:31:22.214
on a moving bus.

526
00:31:22.381 --> 00:31:23.591
This is just one guy.

527
00:31:23.758 --> 00:31:26.218
Just do it.
Then we all get paid.

528
00:31:26.385 --> 00:31:29.305
and then I'll help you find
whoever you're looking for.

529
00:31:29.513 --> 00:31:30.973
Come on. You got this.

530
00:31:31.057 --> 00:31:32.433
- JON JON: You got this.
- Don't be nervous.

531
00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:33.601
Thank you.

532
00:31:33.684 --> 00:31:34.769
- KATY: Yeah.
- Yeah.

533
00:31:36.395 --> 00:31:38.105
(MEN GRUNTING)

534
00:31:38.189 --> 00:31:40.024
(EMIL GROANING)

535
00:31:41.901 --> 00:31:44.028
- How's the jaw?
- (EMIL GRUNTS)

536
00:31:46.155 --> 00:31:48.157
Maybe you'll start
controlling those punches

537
00:31:48.240 --> 00:31:49.575
like we practised?

538
00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:51.327
(EMIL GRUNTING)

539
00:31:55.081 --> 00:31:56.415
Love that guy.

540
00:31:57.958 --> 00:31:59.376
Now take your shirt off.

541
00:31:59.919 --> 00:32:01.837
- (BELL CLANGS)
- JON JON: <i>Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

542
00:32:01.921 --> 00:32:04.256
<i>the fight we've all
been waiting for.</i>

543
00:32:04.715 --> 00:32:07.134
<i>The incredible
viral sensation.</i>

544
00:32:07.301 --> 00:32:11.263
<i>all the way
from San Francisco. USA.</i>

545
00:32:11.680 --> 00:32:14.683
<i>it's Bus Boy!</i>

546
00:32:14.850 --> 00:32:16.435
(SCATTERED CHEERING)

547
00:32:18.687 --> 00:32:20.481
What happened to your shirt?

548
00:32:21.816 --> 00:32:24.235
(TRADITIONAL DRUM MUSIC
PLAYING ON SPEAKER)

549
00:32:24.944 --> 00:32:27.571
JON JON: <i>And his opponent
for tonight.</i>

550
00:32:28.114 --> 00:32:31.158
<i>it's Macau's
own fearsome killer...</i>

551
00:32:33.452 --> 00:32:37.456
<i>XuXialing!</i>

552
00:32:37.540 --> 00:32:39.542
(CROWD CHEERING LOUDLY)

553
00:32:42.169 --> 00:32:43.504
(IN MANDARIN) Sister.

554
00:32:44.130 --> 00:32:45.172
(GRUNTS)

555
00:32:45.422 --> 00:32:46.590
(IN ENGLISH) Wait. wait!

556
00:32:48.759 --> 00:32:49.802
(IN MANDARIN) What are you doing?

557
00:32:50.010 --> 00:32:51.762
(BOTH GRUNTING)

558
00:32:56.934 --> 00:32:58.561
I know you're upset.

559
00:32:58.727 --> 00:33:00.229
But can you hear me out?

560
00:33:04.233 --> 00:33:05.985
We don't have time for this.

561
00:33:15.286 --> 00:33:16.579
JON JON: (IN ENGLISH)
<i>Ooh. that's gotta hurt.</i>

562
00:33:23.294 --> 00:33:25.588
(IN MANDARIN)
Can you please stop hitting me?

563
00:33:35.931 --> 00:33:38.934
Stop it! I'm trying to help you!

564
00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:41.729
Dad's coming for you.

565
00:33:46.066 --> 00:33:47.651
I'm not fighting you.

566
00:33:48.569 --> 00:33:50.905
You shouldn't have come back.

567
00:33:56.410 --> 00:34:00.331
YOUNG XIALING:
Sometimes when I'm doing my forms...

568
00:34:01.624 --> 00:34:03.626
I close my eyes.

569
00:34:03.792 --> 00:34:07.796
and it's like I can feel her.

570
00:34:08.589 --> 00:34:10.883
Do you ever feel like that?

571
00:34:12.885 --> 00:34:14.720
No.

572
00:34:18.641 --> 00:34:20.893
(IN ENGLISH) I know
what you're going there to do.

573
00:34:22.019 --> 00:34:23.854
I don't know what
he's telling you. but Mom...

574
00:34:24.021 --> 00:34:25.648
Mom's dead.

575
00:34:27.816 --> 00:34:28.817
(SNIFFLES)

576
00:34:30.152 --> 00:34:31.987
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

577
00:34:38.369 --> 00:34:40.537
(IN MANDARIN)
Please don't leave me here.

578
00:34:41.872 --> 00:34:43.165
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

579
00:34:47.586 --> 00:34:50.631
I'll be back in three days.

580
00:34:54.885 --> 00:34:56.637
(SIGHING)

581
00:35:07.439 --> 00:35:08.565
(SHANG-CHI GRUNTS)

582
00:35:12.027 --> 00:35:14.113
(CROWD CHEERING)

583
00:35:14.196 --> 00:35:15.864
JON JON: (IN ENGLISH)
<i>XuXialing. you're amazing!</i>

584
00:35:16.031 --> 00:35:17.700
<i>We love you. XuXialing!
Whoo!</i>

585
00:35:18.242 --> 00:35:19.326
(GROANS)

586
00:35:19.410 --> 00:35:21.578
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKER)

587
00:35:21.704 --> 00:35:23.414
(CROWD CONTINUES CHEERING)

588
00:35:34.967 --> 00:35:36.468
(IN MANDARIN) You run this place?

589
00:35:37.094 --> 00:35:39.013
I own it.

590
00:35:39.221 --> 00:35:40.222
(DOOR BEEPS)

591
00:35:42.182 --> 00:35:43.767
(IN ENGLISH) Where'd you
get all that money?

592
00:35:44.977 --> 00:35:46.437
Did you bet against me?

593
00:35:47.187 --> 00:35:48.188
No.

594
00:35:49.690 --> 00:35:51.108
Hi. Xialing. I'm Katy.

595
00:35:51.275 --> 00:35:52.526
You're. like. such a badass.

596
00:35:52.609 --> 00:35:53.861
Everything that you do is.
like. so cool.

597
00:35:54.028 --> 00:35:55.195
That was really cool.

598
00:35:55.821 --> 00:35:56.822
I like your pants.

599
00:35:56.989 --> 00:35:58.824
Thank you. Thanks. Yeah.

600
00:36:00.534 --> 00:36:01.744
What do you want?

601
00:36:01.910 --> 00:36:04.163
The Ten Rings ambushed us
in San Francisco.

602
00:36:04.330 --> 00:36:05.497
XIALING: I saw the video.

603
00:36:05.664 --> 00:36:07.041
They took my pendant.

604
00:36:08.208 --> 00:36:09.752
They're gonna come
for yours next.

605
00:36:12.546 --> 00:36:13.881
I don't know
what he wants with them.

606
00:36:14.048 --> 00:36:15.507
but we both know
it can't be good.

607
00:36:19.803 --> 00:36:21.805
You know what he said to me
when he left?

608
00:36:22.848 --> 00:36:25.267
"I'll be back in three days."

609
00:36:26.769 --> 00:36:27.770
And after three days.

610
00:36:27.853 --> 00:36:30.022
I went to our mom's shrine
and waited.

611
00:36:32.566 --> 00:36:34.401
Three days
turned into a week.

612
00:36:35.069 --> 00:36:36.612
a week turned to a month.

613
00:36:36.695 --> 00:36:38.947
and a month
turned to six years.

614
00:36:44.411 --> 00:36:45.871
That's how long
it took me to realise

615
00:36:45.954 --> 00:36:47.664
I didn't need him any more.

616
00:36:49.958 --> 00:36:52.711
I built this place on my own.

617
00:36:53.003 --> 00:36:56.840
I didn't need you then.
and I don't need you now.

618
00:36:58.634 --> 00:37:00.552
Then why would you
send me the postcard?

619
00:37:01.011 --> 00:37:02.388
XIALING: What postcard?

620
00:37:10.521 --> 00:37:12.064
I didn't send you this.

621
00:37:13.690 --> 00:37:16.110
- (DISTANT EXPLOSION)
- (CROWD SCREAMING)

622
00:37:16.193 --> 00:37:17.736
(ALARM BLARING)

623
00:37:19.363 --> 00:37:20.781
Is there a back exit?

624
00:37:21.240 --> 00:37:22.366
Shaun.

625
00:37:23.200 --> 00:37:25.994
SHANG-CHI: Hey. Hey!
Hey. open up!

626
00:37:30.666 --> 00:37:31.875
She's gone. dude.

627
00:37:32.835 --> 00:37:34.253
(MUFFLED EXPLOSION)

628
00:37:36.004 --> 00:37:38.006
(PANICKED CHATTER)

629
00:37:43.345 --> 00:37:44.388
(MAN GROANS)

630
00:37:45.347 --> 00:37:46.432
(GRUNTS)

631
00:37:48.642 --> 00:37:49.643
What do we do?

632
00:37:49.810 --> 00:37:51.228
What do we do?

633
00:37:51.562 --> 00:37:52.563
Uh...

634
00:37:53.522 --> 00:37:54.731
(GRUNTS)

635
00:37:58.735 --> 00:38:00.112
Come on!

636
00:38:05.075 --> 00:38:07.202
Oh. hell no. Screw you!
I'm not doing this.

637
00:38:07.369 --> 00:38:08.370
If we make it to the elevator.

638
00:38:08.454 --> 00:38:09.663
we can hop in
on the next floor.

639
00:38:09.746 --> 00:38:11.081
- (MUFFLED EXPLOSION)
- (CROWD SCREAMING)

640
00:38:11.165 --> 00:38:13.000
Katy. we're out of options.
We have to go now.

641
00:38:15.919 --> 00:38:18.213
One. two. three.

642
00:38:20.466 --> 00:38:21.467
KATY: Whoa.

643
00:38:23.969 --> 00:38:25.262
SHANG-CHI: Just head
straight for that elevator.

644
00:38:26.388 --> 00:38:27.556
You got this.

645
00:38:39.443 --> 00:38:41.028
I'll buy you some time.
Just keep going.

646
00:38:42.279 --> 00:38:44.531
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

647
00:38:49.119 --> 00:38:50.871
(ALL GRUNTING)

648
00:38:59.838 --> 00:39:01.173
(FIGHTER SCREAMS)

649
00:39:11.225 --> 00:39:12.392
(FIGHTER 2 SCREAMS)

650
00:39:16.188 --> 00:39:17.523
- (CRACKLING)
- (GROANS)

651
00:39:22.319 --> 00:39:23.362
(GRUNTS)

652
00:39:31.245 --> 00:39:33.455
(SINGING <i>HOTEL CALIFORNIA</i> BY EAGLES)
<i>On a dark desert highway</i>

653
00:39:34.206 --> 00:39:36.124
<i>Cool wind in my hair</i>

654
00:39:40.671 --> 00:39:42.673
(YELLING)

655
00:39:45.092 --> 00:39:46.260
Shaun!

656
00:39:46.343 --> 00:39:47.761
(FIGHTER 3 SCREAMING)

657
00:39:49.096 --> 00:39:51.515
Shaun! Shaun!

658
00:39:54.977 --> 00:39:56.728
Oh. my God! Ohhh!

659
00:39:58.522 --> 00:40:00.107
(ALL GRUNTING)

660
00:40:01.733 --> 00:40:02.776
SHANG-CHI: I'm coming!

661
00:40:05.654 --> 00:40:06.863
(KATY YELLS)

662
00:40:08.031 --> 00:40:09.283
KATY: Shaun!

663
00:40:10.450 --> 00:40:11.618
SHANG-CHI: Hang on.

664
00:40:12.578 --> 00:40:13.620
(KATY YELPING)

665
00:40:14.371 --> 00:40:16.123
(STRAINING) Gotcha.

666
00:40:16.623 --> 00:40:17.624
Shaun!

667
00:40:17.708 --> 00:40:18.750
(GROANS)

668
00:40:19.376 --> 00:40:20.669
Katy!

669
00:40:23.672 --> 00:40:25.549
(KATY GRUNTING)

670
00:40:30.596 --> 00:40:31.805
(FIGHTER 4 YELLS)

671
00:40:34.766 --> 00:40:36.768
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

672
00:40:39.938 --> 00:40:41.273
(ALL GRUNTING)

673
00:40:45.068 --> 00:40:46.570
(IN MANDARIN) You left us for dead!

674
00:40:48.655 --> 00:40:50.616
Now you know how it feels.

675
00:40:57.914 --> 00:40:59.333
(FIGHTER 5 SCREAMS)

676
00:41:05.756 --> 00:41:06.840
(GRUNTS)

677
00:41:09.885 --> 00:41:11.011
(IN ENGLISH) What does
he want with the pendant...

678
00:41:11.720 --> 00:41:13.347
(SCREAMING)

679
00:41:17.100 --> 00:41:18.727
Did America make you soft?

680
00:41:20.187 --> 00:41:21.938
- (GLASS THUDS)
- (BEEPING RAPIDLY)

681
00:41:23.732 --> 00:41:25.108
(BOTH GRUNTING)

682
00:41:32.324 --> 00:41:33.617
(XIALING YELPS)

683
00:41:33.700 --> 00:41:35.118
XIALING: He has the pendant!

684
00:41:38.372 --> 00:41:40.207
(GRUNTING)

685
00:41:42.834 --> 00:41:44.544
(PANTING)

686
00:41:49.758 --> 00:41:50.884
(EXPLOSION)

687
00:41:57.641 --> 00:41:58.642
(GRUNTS)

688
00:42:00.519 --> 00:42:01.895
(BOTH GRUNTING)

689
00:42:23.625 --> 00:42:25.544
(BOTH STRAINING)

690
00:42:38.473 --> 00:42:40.475
- (SHANG-CHI PANTING)
- (GRUNTING)

691
00:42:44.813 --> 00:42:45.939
(GRUNTS)

692
00:42:59.202 --> 00:43:00.203
I told my men

693
00:43:00.287 --> 00:43:03.623
they wouldn't be able
to kill you if they tried.

694
00:43:04.875 --> 00:43:06.334
Glad I was right.

695
00:43:12.007 --> 00:43:14.676
(IN MANDARIN) I've missed you. my son.

696
00:43:18.889 --> 00:43:20.348
(IN ENGLISH) Let's go home.

697
00:43:20.432 --> 00:43:22.768
(SOMBRE ORCHESTRAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

698
00:43:37.324 --> 00:43:39.576
(SOMBRE MUSIC CONTINUES)

699
00:44:00.555 --> 00:44:02.766
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

700
00:44:19.157 --> 00:44:20.534
My son is home.

701
00:44:25.121 --> 00:44:26.581
Take the girls to their room.

702
00:44:37.259 --> 00:44:39.886
I've seen some really
scary stuff this week.

703
00:44:40.053 --> 00:44:43.056
but your dad's on.
like. a whole 'nother level.

704
00:44:44.766 --> 00:44:46.476
Is he gonna kill us?

705
00:44:47.853 --> 00:44:51.398
Just nod. Don't talk.
He'll forget you're there.

706
00:44:51.940 --> 00:44:53.817
That's how I survived.

707
00:44:54.901 --> 00:44:56.820
He always treat you like that?

708
00:44:58.738 --> 00:45:00.907
Only after my mom died.

709
00:45:02.868 --> 00:45:07.289
He said he couldn't look at me
because I reminded him of her.

710
00:45:08.874 --> 00:45:11.084
I wasn't allowed to train
with the boys.

711
00:45:12.377 --> 00:45:14.129
But I watched
everything they did

712
00:45:14.212 --> 00:45:16.256
and taught myself
to do it better.

713
00:45:18.592 --> 00:45:19.968
When did you leave?

714
00:45:20.135 --> 00:45:22.387
I ran away when I was 16.

715
00:45:22.804 --> 00:45:25.432
As soon as I knew
my brother wasn't coming back.

716
00:45:26.349 --> 00:45:29.352
You started an underground
fight ring in Macau

717
00:45:29.978 --> 00:45:31.730
when you were 16 years old?

718
00:45:33.189 --> 00:45:36.151
If my dad won't let me
into his empire.

719
00:45:36.234 --> 00:45:37.694
I'm gonna build my own.

720
00:45:38.987 --> 00:45:40.322
Hell yeah.

721
00:45:49.414 --> 00:45:51.625
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

722
00:45:56.922 --> 00:45:59.132
(GRUNTING)

723
00:46:06.681 --> 00:46:07.682
MAN: Shang-Chi.

724
00:46:10.226 --> 00:46:12.103
(IN MANDARIN) That's enough.

725
00:46:18.401 --> 00:46:20.862
(IN ENGLISH) Have you been
practicing your English?

726
00:46:23.031 --> 00:46:24.157
Yes.

727
00:46:26.159 --> 00:46:29.829
You have to strengthen your
mind along with your body.

728
00:46:36.211 --> 00:46:39.756
If you want them
to be yours one day.

729
00:46:39.923 --> 00:46:43.843
you have to show me you're
strong enough to carry them.

730
00:46:48.223 --> 00:46:50.225
(GRUNTING)

731
00:46:59.818 --> 00:47:00.986
(SIGHS)

732
00:47:01.444 --> 00:47:02.946
How did you find me?

733
00:47:03.738 --> 00:47:05.991
I always know
where my children are.

734
00:47:06.950 --> 00:47:08.785
I gave you 10 years
to live your life.

735
00:47:08.868 --> 00:47:10.161
and where did it get you?

736
00:47:10.870 --> 00:47:11.871
(SHANG-CHI SIGHS)

737
00:47:13.415 --> 00:47:17.252
Now it's time for you
to take your place by my side.

738
00:47:18.253 --> 00:47:20.588
That's not gonna happen.

739
00:47:24.092 --> 00:47:25.719
MAN: American girl.

740
00:47:25.885 --> 00:47:27.012
Her name is Katy.

741
00:47:28.304 --> 00:47:29.973
What is your Chinese name?

742
00:47:33.977 --> 00:47:35.270
Ruiwen.

743
00:47:36.312 --> 00:47:38.481
Names are sacred. Ruiwen.

744
00:47:38.648 --> 00:47:40.650
They connect us
not only to ourselves.

745
00:47:40.734 --> 00:47:42.527
but to everyone
who came before.

746
00:47:43.987 --> 00:47:45.655
A funny story.

747
00:47:45.822 --> 00:47:48.283
Some years ago.
a terrorist from America

748
00:47:48.366 --> 00:47:49.784
needed a boogeyman

749
00:47:49.951 --> 00:47:52.579
to bring your country
to its knees.

750
00:47:52.746 --> 00:47:55.415
So. he appropriated
The Ten Rings.

751
00:47:55.498 --> 00:47:56.499
My Ten Rings.

752
00:47:56.583 --> 00:47:59.085
But because
he didn't know my actual name.

753
00:47:59.169 --> 00:48:00.545
he invented a new one.

754
00:48:01.171 --> 00:48:03.131
Do you know the name he chose?

755
00:48:04.966 --> 00:48:06.509
The Mandarin.

756
00:48:06.676 --> 00:48:09.637
He gave his figurehead
the name of a chicken dish.

757
00:48:10.055 --> 00:48:11.473
And it worked.

758
00:48:11.639 --> 00:48:13.433
America was terrified.

759
00:48:14.309 --> 00:48:15.894
Of an orange.

760
00:48:16.603 --> 00:48:17.604
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

761
00:48:17.687 --> 00:48:18.980
The truth is.

762
00:48:19.147 --> 00:48:22.025
I've had many names
throughout my life.

763
00:48:22.734 --> 00:48:25.153
The Warrior King. Master Khan.

764
00:48:25.236 --> 00:48:27.363
the most dangerous man
on Earth.

765
00:48:27.697 --> 00:48:31.743
For years. I thought that was
all I was meant to be.

766
00:48:34.579 --> 00:48:37.457
But when I met their mother.

767
00:48:38.208 --> 00:48:40.001
everything changed.

768
00:48:41.044 --> 00:48:43.338
(SOFT TRADITIONAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

769
00:48:46.216 --> 00:48:47.300
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

770
00:48:54.224 --> 00:48:57.852
<i>She showed me a part of myself
I didn't know was there.</i>

771
00:49:00.605 --> 00:49:03.483
<i>It was like I was seeing
the world for the first time.</i>

772
00:49:03.566 --> 00:49:05.568
(CONVERSING IN MANDARIN)

773
00:49:13.660 --> 00:49:17.205
<i>She gave up everything
so we could be together.</i>

774
00:49:20.458 --> 00:49:22.127
<i>And so did I.</i>

775
00:49:23.670 --> 00:49:25.338
- (LI GIGGLES)
- (CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

776
00:49:37.183 --> 00:49:38.852
(IN MANDARIN)You know who's in there?

777
00:49:39.018 --> 00:49:40.854
Say. "Hello. little sister!"

778
00:49:45.567 --> 00:49:46.568
(LI GIGGLES)

779
00:49:47.318 --> 00:49:48.778
MANDARIN:
<i>After all those years.</i>

780
00:49:48.862 --> 00:49:50.446
<i>I finally found something</i>

781
00:49:50.613 --> 00:49:52.782
<i>worth growing old for.</i>

782
00:49:58.246 --> 00:50:00.623
My real name is Wenwu.

783
00:50:01.457 --> 00:50:04.043
She was the only one
who called me that.

784
00:50:05.712 --> 00:50:07.505
And when she died...

785
00:50:10.717 --> 00:50:13.052
I was lost for many years.

786
00:50:15.763 --> 00:50:17.765
But I'm not lost any more.

787
00:50:22.145 --> 00:50:23.605
When you children ran away.

788
00:50:23.771 --> 00:50:26.316
I was so desperate
to connect with your mother.

789
00:50:26.482 --> 00:50:29.694
I threw myself back into
the studies of her village.

790
00:50:30.278 --> 00:50:32.071
The legendary Ta Lo.

791
00:50:33.281 --> 00:50:34.449
I wasn't able

792
00:50:34.532 --> 00:50:36.784
to find the secret path
to the village entrance.

793
00:50:36.951 --> 00:50:40.496
but I did find
what they are hiding.

794
00:50:41.039 --> 00:50:43.583
There's a gate
deep in their mountains.

795
00:50:44.250 --> 00:50:46.920
Your mother
is waiting for us there.

796
00:50:49.881 --> 00:50:51.507
I know this is a lot.

797
00:50:51.716 --> 00:50:55.553
I might not have believed it
if she didn't tell me herself.

798
00:50:56.387 --> 00:50:58.014
What are you talking about?

799
00:50:58.514 --> 00:51:00.600
I was sitting right here
in this seat.

800
00:51:01.017 --> 00:51:03.061
deep in my research...

801
00:51:04.270 --> 00:51:06.147
and she spoke to me.

802
00:51:06.940 --> 00:51:09.692
It was like
she was standing in this room.

803
00:51:09.859 --> 00:51:12.695
I could feel her breath
on my cheek

804
00:51:12.779 --> 00:51:14.739
and her hand on my back.

805
00:51:16.282 --> 00:51:18.534
She told me she needs my help.

806
00:51:20.286 --> 00:51:21.496
To do what?

807
00:51:22.288 --> 00:51:24.666
To save her from her people.

808
00:51:27.835 --> 00:51:29.671
After we fell in love.

809
00:51:29.754 --> 00:51:32.465
your mother wanted us
to live in Ta Lo.

810
00:51:32.632 --> 00:51:34.634
She asked permission
from the elders.

811
00:51:34.717 --> 00:51:35.885
and they refused.

812
00:51:36.052 --> 00:51:38.263
They said I wasn't worthy.

813
00:51:40.056 --> 00:51:41.391
She would still be with us.

814
00:51:41.474 --> 00:51:44.102
We would all be
living there together.

815
00:51:44.894 --> 00:51:46.604
Ta Lo did this to us.

816
00:51:48.398 --> 00:51:51.025
They locked her behind
that gate to punish her.

817
00:51:55.446 --> 00:51:56.698
Don't you see?

818
00:51:57.657 --> 00:51:59.742
She's leaving clues for us.

819
00:51:59.909 --> 00:52:01.369
She wants us to find her

820
00:52:01.536 --> 00:52:04.289
and bring her home.
so we can be a family again.

821
00:52:05.164 --> 00:52:07.834
Dad. Mom's gone.

822
00:52:09.168 --> 00:52:11.129
She's not talking to you
from behind a gate.

823
00:52:11.212 --> 00:52:13.506
and she's not leaving
any clues for us.

824
00:52:18.845 --> 00:52:20.847
Then what are these?

825
00:52:34.861 --> 00:52:37.030
(MYSTICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

826
00:52:38.531 --> 00:52:40.325
(SOFT WHOOSHING)

827
00:53:07.352 --> 00:53:11.022
The passage to Ta Lo
is guarded by a moving maze.

828
00:53:12.065 --> 00:53:15.193
But there's a direct path
through the forest

829
00:53:15.276 --> 00:53:17.362
that only opens once a year

830
00:53:17.528 --> 00:53:19.447
on Qingming Jie.

831
00:53:20.406 --> 00:53:22.950
To get through.
you need to know the route

832
00:53:23.034 --> 00:53:25.411
and the exact time it opens.

833
00:53:29.832 --> 00:53:31.459
Now I know both.

834
00:53:43.221 --> 00:53:45.264
Three days from now.

835
00:53:45.431 --> 00:53:47.809
we will rescue
my wife from her prison

836
00:53:47.892 --> 00:53:49.102
and bring her home.

837
00:53:49.185 --> 00:53:50.686
(ALL RESPOND IN MANDARIN)

838
00:53:55.775 --> 00:53:57.443
This is why you're here.

839
00:53:58.361 --> 00:53:59.946
To help me
bring her back to us.

840
00:54:00.530 --> 00:54:02.824
And what happens if they don't
let you open the gate?

841
00:54:04.450 --> 00:54:07.870
We'll burn the village
to the ground.

842
00:54:09.914 --> 00:54:10.915
What?

843
00:54:13.626 --> 00:54:15.920
You can't just march
into our mom's village

844
00:54:16.003 --> 00:54:17.422
with this bullshit.

845
00:54:17.839 --> 00:54:19.298
I mean. do you have
any idea how insane...

846
00:54:19.715 --> 00:54:21.259
(SHANG-CHI GRUNTING)

847
00:54:21.342 --> 00:54:22.343
(GASPS)

848
00:54:24.637 --> 00:54:25.638
Hey!

849
00:54:25.847 --> 00:54:27.515
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

850
00:54:28.516 --> 00:54:31.060
Where are you taking me?

851
00:54:32.437 --> 00:54:34.730
(IN MANDARIN)
When will you stop pretending?

852
00:54:37.442 --> 00:54:38.609
(IN ENGLISH) Lock them up.

853
00:54:58.254 --> 00:55:01.424
LI: (IN MANDARIN) It's okay. my dear.

854
00:55:08.347 --> 00:55:12.518
We're all going to be
together soon.

855
00:55:21.110 --> 00:55:25.907
(IN ENGLISH) So. um.
pretty confused right now.

856
00:55:26.073 --> 00:55:29.619
because. uh. initially
I thought your dad should

857
00:55:29.827 --> 00:55:31.746
definitely see a therapist
for his delusions.

858
00:55:31.954 --> 00:55:35.541
but then that dragon
vomited a magical water map.

859
00:55:36.292 --> 00:55:38.669
and now I have no idea
what's real.

860
00:55:41.088 --> 00:55:43.424
Is what he said
about your mom's village true?

861
00:55:45.593 --> 00:55:47.053
(SIGHS)

862
00:55:47.136 --> 00:55:48.554
She used to tell us stories
about Ta Lo

863
00:55:48.638 --> 00:55:49.639
when we were kids.

864
00:55:50.681 --> 00:55:54.894
A village in another dimension
full of magical creatures.

865
00:55:54.977 --> 00:55:56.979
I thought
it was just a fairy tale.

866
00:55:58.940 --> 00:56:00.775
What if Dad's right?

867
00:56:02.568 --> 00:56:03.903
About Mom being locked
behind a gate

868
00:56:03.986 --> 00:56:05.947
by her own people?

869
00:56:06.113 --> 00:56:08.366
Crazier things
have turned out to be true.

870
00:56:09.575 --> 00:56:11.744
Look. I don't know
what the hell is going on.

871
00:56:11.911 --> 00:56:14.330
but if we don't find a way
to get to Ta Lo before him.

872
00:56:14.497 --> 00:56:16.916
he's gonna destroy everything
that's left of our family.

873
00:56:19.210 --> 00:56:22.088
This family was destroyed
a long time ago.

874
00:56:23.506 --> 00:56:25.383
(MUFFLED MAN GROANING)

875
00:56:26.384 --> 00:56:28.052
The hell was that?

876
00:56:28.135 --> 00:56:30.304
- (GROANING AND GIBBERING)
- Oh.

877
00:56:30.388 --> 00:56:32.640
(FUMBLES) You're going
toward that noise?

878
00:56:32.974 --> 00:56:35.935
(MAN CONTINUES GROANING
AND GIBBERING)

879
00:56:39.397 --> 00:56:41.732
(METAL STRIKING)

880
00:56:52.159 --> 00:56:55.454
"Wake Duncan
with thy knocking.

881
00:56:55.621 --> 00:56:58.583
"Oh. I would'st
though could'st.

882
00:56:58.749 --> 00:57:00.293
"My deed 'twere best not..."

883
00:57:03.296 --> 00:57:05.256
Oh. hello. loves.

884
00:57:06.382 --> 00:57:07.842
What year is it?

885
00:57:09.343 --> 00:57:10.720
Who are you?

886
00:57:10.886 --> 00:57:13.014
Trevor? Slattery?

887
00:57:13.180 --> 00:57:15.600
The actor from Liverpool?

888
00:57:16.517 --> 00:57:17.518
Wait.

889
00:57:17.685 --> 00:57:19.228
Are you the governor's kids?

890
00:57:19.895 --> 00:57:21.522
I've been preparing
a monologue

891
00:57:21.606 --> 00:57:23.274
for your homecoming dinner.

892
00:57:23.441 --> 00:57:25.318
Oh. Where's she going?

893
00:57:25.484 --> 00:57:26.652
Why are you down here?

894
00:57:26.819 --> 00:57:28.779
Well. some time ago.

895
00:57:28.863 --> 00:57:30.406
I was offered
the role of a terrorist.

896
00:57:30.615 --> 00:57:32.867
I know. facile. trite.
I couldn't agree more.

897
00:57:33.034 --> 00:57:34.952
But times were lean.
you know what I mean?

898
00:57:35.119 --> 00:57:37.872
Anyway. the producer told me
he worked for the BBC.

899
00:57:38.039 --> 00:57:39.498
But. ironic twist.

900
00:57:39.582 --> 00:57:42.168
it turns out he. in fact.
was a terrorist.

901
00:57:42.335 --> 00:57:43.836
and I wasn't playing
a character at all.

902
00:57:44.003 --> 00:57:45.296
but what I now recognise to be

903
00:57:45.379 --> 00:57:47.340
a rather unflattering portrait
of your father.

904
00:57:47.757 --> 00:57:49.508
We all got our just deserts.

905
00:57:49.675 --> 00:57:51.552
The producer
got blown up by Iron Man.

906
00:57:51.636 --> 00:57:53.304
and I served time
in federal prison.

907
00:57:53.471 --> 00:57:56.307
which turned out
to be the best thing for me.

908
00:57:56.390 --> 00:57:58.809
I got clean.
I rediscovered my passion.

909
00:57:58.976 --> 00:58:01.562
- Then my dad broke you out?
- Exactly.

910
00:58:01.729 --> 00:58:03.814
- To kill you.
- Exactly.

911
00:58:04.565 --> 00:58:06.901
But just as his men

912
00:58:06.984 --> 00:58:09.612
were tying me up
for my execution.

913
00:58:09.779 --> 00:58:11.656
I launched into a performance
of my Macbeth.

914
00:58:11.739 --> 00:58:13.366
"Whence is that knocking?
Wake Duncan

915
00:58:13.449 --> 00:58:14.950
"with thy knocking.
I would'st though could'st..."

916
00:58:15.034 --> 00:58:16.202
They couldn't
get enough of it.

917
00:58:16.369 --> 00:58:18.788
I've been doing weekly gigs
for the lads ever since.

918
00:58:18.954 --> 00:58:20.831
So you're like his jester?

919
00:58:20.998 --> 00:58:22.667
I can give you a quick preview
if you like.

920
00:58:22.750 --> 00:58:24.001
"Nuncle. nuncle. nuncle..."

921
00:58:24.168 --> 00:58:26.462
Uh. thank you. Trevor.
I think we're okay.

922
00:58:26.671 --> 00:58:28.506
Right now. we really just
need to find a way to...

923
00:58:28.589 --> 00:58:30.007
- (CREATURE PURRING)
- What the hell?

924
00:58:30.091 --> 00:58:31.217
KATY: What the... Oh!

925
00:58:31.300 --> 00:58:32.343
- Whoa!
- What is that?

926
00:58:32.426 --> 00:58:33.969
(KATY EXCLAIMING)

927
00:58:34.053 --> 00:58:35.054
What's what?

928
00:58:35.221 --> 00:58:37.014
- That! What is that?
- That! That! That!

929
00:58:37.348 --> 00:58:38.641
(CREATURE COOS)

930
00:58:39.350 --> 00:58:40.685
You can see Morris?

931
00:58:40.851 --> 00:58:41.852
KATY: Morris?

932
00:58:41.936 --> 00:58:44.605
(LAUGHS) Oh. Morris!

933
00:58:44.772 --> 00:58:47.108
They can see you! You're real!

934
00:58:47.274 --> 00:58:50.319
All this time I thought
I was hallucinating him.

935
00:58:50.486 --> 00:58:51.987
Oh. this is such fab news.

936
00:58:53.072 --> 00:58:54.073
Where's his face?

937
00:58:54.156 --> 00:58:55.616
- (MORRIS GROWLS)
- (SHUSHING)

938
00:58:55.700 --> 00:58:57.368
He's a bit sensitive
about that.

939
00:58:58.494 --> 00:59:00.204
- (MORRIS CHITTERING)
- Oh. Really?

940
00:59:01.831 --> 00:59:03.457
Morris says he knows
who you are.

941
00:59:04.166 --> 00:59:05.501
It talks... It talks to you?

942
00:59:05.584 --> 00:59:07.128
(CHUCKLES)
if he didn't talk to me.

943
00:59:07.211 --> 00:59:09.046
I'd have gone mad yonks ago.

944
00:59:10.423 --> 00:59:11.799
SHANG-CHI:
How would he know me?

945
00:59:11.966 --> 00:59:14.802
He says he grew up
with your mum. In Ta Lo.

946
00:59:15.678 --> 00:59:18.764
Apparently. your father picked
him up in some magic forest

947
00:59:18.931 --> 00:59:21.642
on one of his expeditions
to find the entrance.

948
00:59:21.726 --> 00:59:24.061
(MORRIS PURRING AND COOING)

949
00:59:25.312 --> 00:59:26.897
He wants you to take him home.

950
00:59:26.981 --> 00:59:28.816
(MORRIS COOING)

951
00:59:29.483 --> 00:59:31.527
Believe me. buddy.
I would if I knew how.

952
00:59:32.236 --> 00:59:33.237
According to my dad.

953
00:59:33.320 --> 00:59:35.072
the path there
only opens once a year.

954
00:59:35.156 --> 00:59:37.158
(MORRIS CHITTERING)

955
00:59:38.576 --> 00:59:40.745
- Oh. (CHUCKLES)
- (CONTINUES CHITTERING)

956
00:59:41.954 --> 00:59:44.540
Morris says he can guide you
there right now.

957
00:59:44.707 --> 00:59:45.916
You can get through the maze

958
00:59:46.000 --> 00:59:47.585
without waiting
for the path to open.

959
00:59:47.752 --> 00:59:49.754
But. and it's a big "but."

960
00:59:49.920 --> 00:59:51.964
it's very dangerous.

961
00:59:52.131 --> 00:59:53.132
How dangerous?

962
00:59:53.299 --> 00:59:55.217
No one's ever
made it out alive.

963
00:59:55.384 --> 00:59:58.179
But Morris is 90% confident

964
00:59:58.345 --> 01:00:00.097
he can guide us
through safely.

965
01:00:00.181 --> 01:00:01.724
- (MORRIS SQUEALS)
- Oh. (CHUCKLES)

966
01:00:01.807 --> 01:00:03.309
19%.

967
01:00:05.811 --> 01:00:08.314
Look. I've done dumber things
with worse odds.

968
01:00:08.481 --> 01:00:10.191
But even if
that chicken-pig is right...

969
01:00:10.274 --> 01:00:11.275
(MORRIS WHINES)

970
01:00:11.358 --> 01:00:12.359
...we're still locked
in your...

971
01:00:12.443 --> 01:00:13.486
(CRASHING)

972
01:00:18.574 --> 01:00:19.700
XIALING: Whew!

973
01:00:22.661 --> 01:00:23.954
How did you...

974
01:00:24.121 --> 01:00:26.540
Dad has a tunnel system
under the whole compound.

975
01:00:26.707 --> 01:00:28.459
That's how
I escaped last time.

976
01:00:28.626 --> 01:00:29.627
Oh.

977
01:00:29.710 --> 01:00:31.754
This will take us
straight to the garage.

978
01:00:33.798 --> 01:00:34.799
(MORRIS COOS)

979
01:00:35.216 --> 01:00:36.592
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

980
01:00:40.846 --> 01:00:41.847
(CAR LOCK BEEPS)

981
01:00:43.474 --> 01:00:45.309
KATY: Oh. my God.

982
01:00:45.476 --> 01:00:46.977
I kinda like this guy.

983
01:00:47.144 --> 01:00:48.979
Just head up that ramp
and through the front gate.

984
01:00:49.146 --> 01:00:50.272
Should be a straight shot.

985
01:00:50.356 --> 01:00:52.066
Figure we got about
30 seconds until he...

986
01:00:52.233 --> 01:00:53.234
Do you mind?

987
01:00:53.400 --> 01:00:55.361
I get sick in the back.
Carsick.

988
01:00:55.444 --> 01:00:56.570
- (MORRIS COOING)
- (SHANG-CHI SIGHS)

989
01:00:58.572 --> 01:00:59.740
That's my car!

990
01:00:59.824 --> 01:01:01.909
(ALARM WAILING)

991
01:01:03.869 --> 01:01:05.246
(TYRES SCREECHING)

992
01:01:05.329 --> 01:01:06.330
God damn it.

993
01:01:06.497 --> 01:01:07.623
Hold on.

994
01:01:07.706 --> 01:01:09.041
(ENGINES REVVING)

995
01:01:09.124 --> 01:01:10.167
Is there another exit?

996
01:01:10.251 --> 01:01:11.502
The other end of the garage.

997
01:01:11.669 --> 01:01:13.170
But we need a fingerprint
to open it.

998
01:01:19.969 --> 01:01:21.303
Incoming!

999
01:01:22.680 --> 01:01:23.806
KATY: Shit!

1000
01:01:26.141 --> 01:01:27.977
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1001
01:01:31.564 --> 01:01:33.190
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1002
01:01:43.409 --> 01:01:44.785
(TYRES SQUEALING)

1003
01:01:45.786 --> 01:01:47.162
KATY: What's happening
back there?

1004
01:01:48.497 --> 01:01:49.582
SHANG-CHI: Doing my best.

1005
01:01:49.707 --> 01:01:51.500
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Scan
hand print for gate access.</i>

1006
01:01:51.584 --> 01:01:53.878
- Hurry up!
- SHANG-CHI: I'm trying!

1007
01:01:56.213 --> 01:01:57.298
<i>Scan hand print
for gate access.</i>

1008
01:01:57.381 --> 01:01:58.382
Shaun!

1009
01:01:59.550 --> 01:02:01.135
<i>Access approved.</i>

1010
01:02:07.850 --> 01:02:08.976
(GASPS)

1011
01:02:10.144 --> 01:02:11.854
(PANTING)

1012
01:02:14.273 --> 01:02:15.482
(DOOR OPENS)

1013
01:02:19.862 --> 01:02:22.281
They will come back
once I bring her home.

1014
01:02:24.116 --> 01:02:25.868
Prepare the men for war.

1015
01:02:26.869 --> 01:02:27.912
Yes. sir.

1016
01:02:32.958 --> 01:02:36.420
TREVOR: The first time
I witnessed pure artistry.

1017
01:02:36.795 --> 01:02:40.549
1968. <i>Planet of the Apes.</i>

1018
01:02:40.716 --> 01:02:42.718
I was sitting in the cinema
next to my mum.

1019
01:02:42.801 --> 01:02:44.261
watching mastery

1020
01:02:44.428 --> 01:02:46.305
unfold before my very eyes.

1021
01:02:46.472 --> 01:02:48.599
After the film. I asked her.

1022
01:02:48.766 --> 01:02:51.185
"How did they get those
monkeys to do those things?"

1023
01:02:51.352 --> 01:02:54.146
And she patted me on the head
and she said.

1024
01:02:54.313 --> 01:02:57.191
"It's not real. pet.
It's just acting."

1025
01:02:57.358 --> 01:02:59.068
That's when I knew.

1026
01:03:00.152 --> 01:03:01.570
If they can teach
those monkeys

1027
01:03:01.654 --> 01:03:03.572
to act that brilliantly.

1028
01:03:04.239 --> 01:03:07.493
just imagine what I could
bring to the world.

1029
01:03:08.077 --> 01:03:09.203
So you became an actor

1030
01:03:09.370 --> 01:03:11.288
because you thought
the monkeys were actually...

1031
01:03:11.455 --> 01:03:14.124
Riding horses? I did. Yes.

1032
01:03:14.291 --> 01:03:15.876
When. in fact.

1033
01:03:15.960 --> 01:03:19.046
they were simply acting
as if they were riding horses.

1034
01:03:19.213 --> 01:03:21.423
I still can't get my head
round it. to be honest.

1035
01:03:22.466 --> 01:03:24.259
Good for you. dude.

1036
01:03:24.802 --> 01:03:28.263
You found your passion
and went for it.

1037
01:03:28.430 --> 01:03:29.515
and eventually used it

1038
01:03:29.598 --> 01:03:31.642
to cripple the US government.
but whatever.

1039
01:03:31.809 --> 01:03:33.769
TREVOR: Yeah.
No. yeah. thanks.

1040
01:03:33.852 --> 01:03:35.854
Um. this is really cool
and all.

1041
01:03:35.938 --> 01:03:37.398
but how long
do we have to sit here?

1042
01:03:37.564 --> 01:03:39.024
Morris is very clear.

1043
01:03:39.608 --> 01:03:41.485
The way through
is all about timing.

1044
01:03:41.986 --> 01:03:43.696
Okay. but how long
are we talking?

1045
01:03:43.862 --> 01:03:45.572
Like. hours? Days?

1046
01:03:45.739 --> 01:03:48.367
Friends.
I am but a transitory vessel

1047
01:03:48.450 --> 01:03:49.868
for the infinite wisdom
of a creature

1048
01:03:50.035 --> 01:03:52.287
far more advanced than
we'll ever truly understand.

1049
01:03:52.913 --> 01:03:54.540
What he sees. what he feels

1050
01:03:54.623 --> 01:03:56.333
of this vast. unknown universe

1051
01:03:56.500 --> 01:03:58.419
is beyond anything
our simple brains can...

1052
01:03:58.502 --> 01:03:59.920
- (MORRIS SQUAWKS)
- Oh. You can go.

1053
01:04:00.337 --> 01:04:01.380
What?

1054
01:04:01.463 --> 01:04:03.257
Go. You can go. He says "go."

1055
01:04:11.015 --> 01:04:13.017
(SOFT SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
PLAYING)

1056
01:04:14.518 --> 01:04:16.103
(TREES CREAKING)

1057
01:04:25.070 --> 01:04:26.155
(MORRIS TRILLS)

1058
01:04:26.488 --> 01:04:27.948
You should speed up.

1059
01:04:28.615 --> 01:04:29.616
What? Why?

1060
01:04:31.827 --> 01:04:32.995
Katy. go. go. go!

1061
01:04:33.078 --> 01:04:34.079
(KATY GASPS)

1062
01:04:34.163 --> 01:04:35.497
(ENGINE ACCELERATES)

1063
01:04:36.999 --> 01:04:38.083
- (MORRIS COOS)
- Morris says.

1064
01:04:38.167 --> 01:04:40.044
- "Hard right on three."
- What?

1065
01:04:40.210 --> 01:04:41.211
TREVOR: Two...

1066
01:04:41.295 --> 01:04:42.296
SHANG-CHI: Hard right where?

1067
01:04:42.379 --> 01:04:43.756
- Now.
- (KATY GRUNTS)

1068
01:04:51.013 --> 01:04:52.306
- (MORRIS TRILLS)
- And left.

1069
01:04:52.389 --> 01:04:53.932
- (KATY GRUNTS)
- (TYRES SCREECHING)

1070
01:04:55.642 --> 01:04:56.643
(ALL GRUNTING)

1071
01:04:56.727 --> 01:04:58.312
It's all about staying
in the pocket.

1072
01:04:58.479 --> 01:05:00.147
- What pocket?
- We're in it now.

1073
01:05:00.314 --> 01:05:01.982
SHANG-CHI: What happens if
we don't stay in the pocket?

1074
01:05:02.149 --> 01:05:03.150
The forest eats us.

1075
01:05:03.317 --> 01:05:04.777
Eats us? What does that mean?

1076
01:05:04.943 --> 01:05:06.487
He says it eats us.
Go left.

1077
01:05:11.116 --> 01:05:12.284
(SHANG-CHI GASPS)

1078
01:05:14.703 --> 01:05:16.747
- SHANG-CHI: Watch your back!
- Stay in the pocket.

1079
01:05:16.914 --> 01:05:18.499
- KATY: How close is it?
- Five metres.

1080
01:05:18.665 --> 01:05:20.417
- TREVOR: Stay in the pocket.
- What is that in feet?

1081
01:05:20.584 --> 01:05:21.585
Really fricking close.

1082
01:05:21.752 --> 01:05:22.753
Stay in the pocket.

1083
01:05:22.920 --> 01:05:24.463
Will you just stop saying.
"Stay in the pocket"?

1084
01:05:24.546 --> 01:05:26.548
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1085
01:05:31.053 --> 01:05:33.180
One last right.
then straight on to the end.

1086
01:05:33.764 --> 01:05:35.265
(ALL GRUNTING)

1087
01:05:41.230 --> 01:05:42.564
You might wanna hurry up.

1088
01:05:42.731 --> 01:05:44.566
What do you think I'm doing?

1089
01:05:46.193 --> 01:05:47.236
We're not gonna make it.

1090
01:05:50.405 --> 01:05:51.990
I'm coming home. Mummy.

1091
01:05:52.074 --> 01:05:53.492
(SHANG-CHI STRAINING)

1092
01:05:58.497 --> 01:05:59.498
(ALL GRUNT)

1093
01:06:00.082 --> 01:06:01.959
(ALL PANTING)

1094
01:06:03.210 --> 01:06:04.211
(MORRIS COOS)

1095
01:06:04.294 --> 01:06:07.256
Morris says.
"Great job. everyone."

1096
01:06:08.674 --> 01:06:11.552
Now. all we have to do
is go through that waterfall.

1097
01:06:11.718 --> 01:06:13.512
and we're pretty much there.

1098
01:06:14.847 --> 01:06:16.223
(SHANG-CHI SIGHS)

1099
01:06:19.393 --> 01:06:21.562
(SOFT TRADITIONAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

1100
01:06:27.151 --> 01:06:28.652
(GLASS TINKLING)

1101
01:06:31.989 --> 01:06:33.866
(MORRIS BABBLES)

1102
01:06:33.949 --> 01:06:36.160
(SOFT TRADITIONAL MUSIC
CONTINUES)

1103
01:06:42.040 --> 01:06:43.542
(WHOOSHING)

1104
01:06:55.929 --> 01:06:57.139
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

1105
01:06:57.222 --> 01:06:59.224
(ENTHRALLING MUSIC PLAYING)

1106
01:07:03.854 --> 01:07:04.897
TREVOR: Bloody hell.

1107
01:07:05.063 --> 01:07:06.815
I think those birds
are on fire.

1108
01:07:06.899 --> 01:07:09.276
- (MORRIS CHITTERING)
- Really? Oh.

1109
01:07:09.568 --> 01:07:11.778
Morris says it's normal.

1110
01:07:11.945 --> 01:07:14.281
They're old mates of his.

1111
01:07:14.364 --> 01:07:16.491
(ENTHRALLING MUSIC CONTINUES)

1112
01:07:27.502 --> 01:07:28.921
(PUP YAPPING)

1113
01:07:30.714 --> 01:07:33.050
(MORRIS CHITTERING
AND CHEERING)

1114
01:07:34.092 --> 01:07:35.928
(ALL CHITTERING AND CHEERING)

1115
01:07:41.558 --> 01:07:42.976
- (KATY GASPS)
- (CAR HALTS)

1116
01:07:48.190 --> 01:07:50.192
That's a weird horse.

1117
01:07:51.610 --> 01:07:53.362
What's it looking at me for?

1118
01:07:56.323 --> 01:07:57.407
(SNORTS)

1119
01:07:59.493 --> 01:08:01.662
(SOFT TRADITIONAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

1120
01:08:15.676 --> 01:08:17.678
(MUSIC RISING)

1121
01:08:24.351 --> 01:08:26.311
(CREATURE GRUNTING)

1122
01:08:29.189 --> 01:08:30.357
(GROWLS)

1123
01:08:33.902 --> 01:08:35.320
(MORRIS CHITTERING)

1124
01:08:56.883 --> 01:08:59.011
(IN MANDARIN) Hi there!

1125
01:08:59.261 --> 01:09:01.179
I am Xu Shang-Chi.

1126
01:09:01.805 --> 01:09:04.599
This is my sister. Xu Xialing.

1127
01:09:04.766 --> 01:09:07.311
We're Ying Li's children.

1128
01:09:11.189 --> 01:09:12.691
This is my friend. Katy.

1129
01:09:12.858 --> 01:09:16.486
Get in your car and go home!

1130
01:09:16.653 --> 01:09:19.156
Please. You don't understand.

1131
01:09:19.781 --> 01:09:20.782
(ALL GRUNT)

1132
01:09:21.783 --> 01:09:23.368
(CREATURE GROWLS)

1133
01:09:24.244 --> 01:09:25.495
- Whoa.
- (WOMAN SPEAKING)

1134
01:09:25.579 --> 01:09:26.997
Guang Bo!

1135
01:09:28.373 --> 01:09:30.542
What are you doing?

1136
01:09:31.168 --> 01:09:33.337
Put down your weapons!

1137
01:09:36.298 --> 01:09:37.966
Shang-Chi.

1138
01:09:38.425 --> 01:09:39.551
Xialing.

1139
01:09:39.718 --> 01:09:42.971
I'm your aunty Nan.

1140
01:09:44.723 --> 01:09:47.434
I've waited so long to meet you.

1141
01:09:57.110 --> 01:09:58.737
You look like your mother.

1142
01:10:06.578 --> 01:10:07.704
(IN ENGLISH) Hi. I'm Katy.

1143
01:10:07.913 --> 01:10:09.289
YING NAN:
Welcome to Ta Lo. Katy.

1144
01:10:09.373 --> 01:10:10.957
Oh. thank you.

1145
01:10:12.834 --> 01:10:14.669
(MORRIS PANTING EXCITEDLY)

1146
01:10:14.753 --> 01:10:16.088
(LAUGHS)

1147
01:10:16.755 --> 01:10:19.257
YING NAN: Look who has found
his way home! (CHUCKLES)

1148
01:10:19.925 --> 01:10:21.176
I'm not a threat.

1149
01:10:21.343 --> 01:10:23.470
Just an entertainer.

1150
01:10:23.637 --> 01:10:25.222
Morris can vouch for me.

1151
01:10:27.182 --> 01:10:28.558
We don't have much time.

1152
01:10:29.017 --> 01:10:30.352
Our father is coming.

1153
01:10:30.435 --> 01:10:31.645
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

1154
01:10:34.481 --> 01:10:36.108
(VILLAGERS CHATTERING)

1155
01:10:38.443 --> 01:10:41.405
YING NAN: Our people have been
here for over 4.000 years.

1156
01:10:41.571 --> 01:10:44.366
preparing for something
we hope will never happen.

1157
01:10:44.533 --> 01:10:47.077
We are the keepers
of the Dark Gate.

1158
01:10:47.244 --> 01:10:49.621
sworn to protect this realm
and yours

1159
01:10:49.704 --> 01:10:52.290
from the evil
that's locked behind it.

1160
01:10:53.125 --> 01:10:55.335
SHANG-CHI: Our dad is coming
here to open that gate.

1161
01:10:55.877 --> 01:10:57.879
He thinks
you're holding our mom there.

1162
01:10:59.172 --> 01:11:00.674
Why would he think that?

1163
01:11:00.841 --> 01:11:02.050
XIALING: She told him.

1164
01:11:02.217 --> 01:11:04.261
He says he can hear her
asking for help.

1165
01:11:06.680 --> 01:11:08.682
Is he wearing the rings?

1166
01:11:08.849 --> 01:11:10.976
SHANG-CHI: He hasn't
taken them off since she died.

1167
01:11:12.894 --> 01:11:14.521
What do they have to do
with all this?

1168
01:11:18.442 --> 01:11:20.527
YING NAN: The realm of Ta Lo
stretches far beyond

1169
01:11:20.610 --> 01:11:22.487
the shores
of our small village.

1170
01:11:22.654 --> 01:11:26.324
We have cities that surpass
any in your universe.

1171
01:11:26.491 --> 01:11:29.202
rich with culture and history.

1172
01:11:29.369 --> 01:11:31.371
Thousands of years ago.

1173
01:11:31.538 --> 01:11:34.791
all of our people
lived in peace and prosperity.

1174
01:11:35.876 --> 01:11:39.004
until the attack
of the Dweller-in-Darkness.

1175
01:11:39.629 --> 01:11:41.047
He came with his army.

1176
01:11:41.131 --> 01:11:44.176
devouring every soul
in their path.

1177
01:11:44.342 --> 01:11:48.013
and with each kill.
they grew stronger.

1178
01:11:48.680 --> 01:11:51.224
After decimating
our largest cities.

1179
01:11:51.391 --> 01:11:54.811
they were headed to
your universe to do the same.

1180
01:11:54.978 --> 01:11:58.356
The leaders of Ta Lo sent
their strongest warriors here

1181
01:11:58.523 --> 01:12:01.735
to stop them from reaching
the portal to your world.

1182
01:12:02.319 --> 01:12:05.447
But our ancestors
were no match for them.

1183
01:12:06.573 --> 01:12:09.576
Until The Great Protector

1184
01:12:09.701 --> 01:12:13.246
joined their fight
and turned the tide.

1185
01:12:13.955 --> 01:12:16.958
Together. they pushed
the Dweller and his army

1186
01:12:17.042 --> 01:12:18.251
into the Dark Gate

1187
01:12:18.418 --> 01:12:20.879
and locked it behind them.

1188
01:12:22.839 --> 01:12:26.259
Our people have guarded
that gate ever since.

1189
01:12:26.426 --> 01:12:29.888
empowered by the magic
of The Great Protector

1190
01:12:30.055 --> 01:12:32.349
and the gift that she gave us.

1191
01:12:39.731 --> 01:12:40.941
(WEAPON POWERS UP)

1192
01:12:42.901 --> 01:12:43.902
(KATY GASPS)

1193
01:12:43.985 --> 01:12:44.986
Dragon scales.

1194
01:12:45.153 --> 01:12:46.821
Makes very good arm our.

1195
01:12:48.949 --> 01:12:50.992
Your father isn't the first
to come here

1196
01:12:51.076 --> 01:12:52.327
to open the Dark Gate.

1197
01:12:52.911 --> 01:12:55.163
Many have tried and failed
over the centuries.

1198
01:12:55.330 --> 01:12:57.666
and they all had one thing
in common.

1199
01:12:57.832 --> 01:12:58.833
They were lured here

1200
01:12:58.917 --> 01:13:01.044
by the voice of something
on the other side.

1201
01:13:01.836 --> 01:13:04.714
A voice that promised them
their greatest desires.

1202
01:13:07.175 --> 01:13:11.346
So you think soul eaters
are talking to our dad?

1203
01:13:12.138 --> 01:13:15.475
They know The Ten Rings have
the power to break them free.

1204
01:13:18.728 --> 01:13:19.729
(KATY GASPS)

1205
01:13:19.813 --> 01:13:20.814
Oh.

1206
01:13:23.441 --> 01:13:25.026
Here you go.

1207
01:13:25.277 --> 01:13:26.278
Oh.

1208
01:13:26.820 --> 01:13:28.280
(IN MANDARIN) To the range.

1209
01:13:29.447 --> 01:13:31.491
(IN ENGLISH) What? Okay.

1210
01:13:32.242 --> 01:13:34.911
Um. looks like I'm gonna go
deliver some dragon arrows.

1211
01:13:35.120 --> 01:13:36.538
Oh. you're gonna deliver
some dragon arrows?

1212
01:13:36.621 --> 01:13:37.914
KATY: Yeah.
Make myself useful. you know.

1213
01:13:38.081 --> 01:13:39.082
Thank you.

1214
01:13:41.126 --> 01:13:42.836
Let's go see your mother.

1215
01:13:45.005 --> 01:13:46.464
(MORRIS BABBLING)

1216
01:13:47.257 --> 01:13:48.758
- (MORRIS YELPS)
- (GROWLING)

1217
01:13:51.845 --> 01:13:53.221
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1218
01:13:57.517 --> 01:14:00.103
I just love how you guys know
exactly what you wanna do.

1219
01:14:00.312 --> 01:14:03.106
and you spend your whole life
getting really good at it.

1220
01:14:03.273 --> 01:14:04.858
I wish I was more like that.

1221
01:14:05.025 --> 01:14:07.110
It's like every time I get
moderately good at something.

1222
01:14:07.277 --> 01:14:09.529
I just quit
and start something new.

1223
01:14:09.696 --> 01:14:11.615
But I just know my own limits.

1224
01:14:11.781 --> 01:14:14.409
and I'm not gonna waste
my time chasing something

1225
01:14:14.492 --> 01:14:16.328
that will ultimately be
a disappointment for me.

1226
01:14:16.411 --> 01:14:17.454
- That's not me.
- (SPEAKING MANDARIN)

1227
01:14:17.537 --> 01:14:18.997
Guang Bo.

1228
01:14:20.248 --> 01:14:21.583
Let her shoot.

1229
01:14:24.961 --> 01:14:28.632
If you aim at nothing.
you hit nothing.

1230
01:14:30.800 --> 01:14:33.053
(SOFT FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)

1231
01:14:52.113 --> 01:14:53.740
YING NAN: (IN ENGLISH)
You were everything to her.

1232
01:14:55.408 --> 01:14:57.869
She knew that one day
you would find your way here

1233
01:14:58.036 --> 01:15:00.789
and asked me to prepare
something for your arrival.

1234
01:15:12.842 --> 01:15:14.678
(MUSIC SWELLING)

1235
01:15:23.353 --> 01:15:25.271
After losing someone like her.

1236
01:15:25.355 --> 01:15:27.982
it's easy to feel alone
in this world.

1237
01:15:28.650 --> 01:15:30.318
But you're not.

1238
01:15:30.485 --> 01:15:32.737
You are children
of this family.

1239
01:15:33.321 --> 01:15:35.657
and I welcome you home.

1240
01:15:43.289 --> 01:15:44.541
(SHANG-CHI SIGHS)

1241
01:15:50.046 --> 01:15:52.048
(SHOUTING SYNCHRONOUSLY)

1242
01:16:03.309 --> 01:16:05.145
(IN MANDARIN) You're not
in your father's house any more.

1243
01:16:06.896 --> 01:16:11.025
In Ta Lo. we train as equals.

1244
01:16:12.777 --> 01:16:16.656
You've been in the shadows
long enough. my child.

1245
01:16:20.577 --> 01:16:22.579
(STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING)

1246
01:16:36.050 --> 01:16:37.260
(IN ENGLISH)
Guang Bo. you saw that?

1247
01:16:38.011 --> 01:16:39.345
That was tight!

1248
01:16:43.141 --> 01:16:45.143
(SOFT FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)

1249
01:16:52.734 --> 01:16:54.652
My mother was the only one
who could beat him.

1250
01:16:56.237 --> 01:16:58.031
Show me how she did it.

1251
01:17:05.288 --> 01:17:06.790
TREVOR: (WHISTLES) No. sorry.

1252
01:17:06.956 --> 01:17:08.541
Sorry. Offside. offside.

1253
01:17:13.129 --> 01:17:14.422
(GRUNTING)

1254
01:17:20.929 --> 01:17:21.971
(SHANG-CHI GRUNTING)

1255
01:17:34.943 --> 01:17:36.027
(GROANS)

1256
01:17:40.198 --> 01:17:41.616
(GRUNTING)

1257
01:17:45.954 --> 01:17:47.288
(PANTING)

1258
01:17:51.084 --> 01:17:52.752
(SHANG-CHI BREATHING HEAVILY)

1259
01:18:09.269 --> 01:18:11.479
YING NAN: Your mother knew
who she was.

1260
01:18:12.230 --> 01:18:13.398
Do you?

1261
01:18:26.035 --> 01:18:27.120
(SHANG-CHI GRUNTS)

1262
01:18:35.128 --> 01:18:36.671
- (GRUNTS)
- (YING NAN GASPS)

1263
01:18:38.047 --> 01:18:39.048
(SCOFFS)

1264
01:18:54.522 --> 01:18:55.982
(MUSIC SWELLING)

1265
01:18:59.068 --> 01:19:00.236
(SHANG-CHI GRUNTING)

1266
01:19:02.113 --> 01:19:03.114
(GROANS)

1267
01:19:03.197 --> 01:19:04.532
(PANTING)

1268
01:19:15.960 --> 01:19:17.045
(SIGHS)

1269
01:19:19.422 --> 01:19:22.467
You are a product
of all who came before you.

1270
01:19:23.426 --> 01:19:27.263
The legacy of your family.
the good and the bad.

1271
01:19:28.056 --> 01:19:30.391
it is all a part
of who you are.

1272
01:19:31.935 --> 01:19:33.227
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1273
01:19:34.771 --> 01:19:36.856
Stop hiding. nephew.

1274
01:19:37.690 --> 01:19:39.734
It only prolongs the pain.

1275
01:19:51.496 --> 01:19:52.705
(MUFFLED CHATTERING)

1276
01:19:52.789 --> 01:19:54.916
(SOFT SENTIMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

1277
01:20:12.183 --> 01:20:14.727
LI: (IN MANDARIN)
We'll be together soon.

1278
01:20:21.150 --> 01:20:22.151
RAZOR FIST: (IN ENGLISH) Sir.

1279
01:20:24.821 --> 01:20:26.322
The men are ready.

1280
01:20:27.365 --> 01:20:29.158
The passage will open at dawn.

1281
01:20:30.118 --> 01:20:31.744
RAZOR FIST:
I'll prepare the vehicles.

1282
01:20:46.426 --> 01:20:47.552
(SIGHS)

1283
01:20:55.893 --> 01:20:57.854
LI: (IN MANDARIN) Lead with your breath.

1284
01:20:58.312 --> 01:21:01.274
Look into your heart.

1285
01:21:01.441 --> 01:21:04.777
the light and the dark.

1286
01:21:04.944 --> 01:21:09.032
To know yourself.

1287
01:21:09.198 --> 01:21:13.119
you must face them both.

1288
01:21:20.835 --> 01:21:23.129
(SOFT SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
PLAYING)

1289
01:21:28.217 --> 01:21:30.136
MAN: Your husband tried to destroy us.

1290
01:21:30.720 --> 01:21:33.389
The Iron Gang is here
to repay that debt.

1291
01:21:34.015 --> 01:21:35.933
My husband is not the man
he used to be.

1292
01:21:36.726 --> 01:21:38.102
GANG LEADER: It doesn't matter.

1293
01:21:39.353 --> 01:21:42.607
Your business with him has nothing
to do with my children.

1294
01:21:45.526 --> 01:21:47.403
They can go.

1295
01:21:47.570 --> 01:21:51.365
but someone has to pay.

1296
01:21:56.037 --> 01:21:57.872
Xialing. Shang-Chi.

1297
01:21:58.039 --> 01:21:59.040
Go inside.

1298
01:21:59.165 --> 01:22:01.959
I'm going to talk to our guests.

1299
01:22:07.965 --> 01:22:10.802
But you don't have your powers.

1300
01:22:13.513 --> 01:22:15.556
Shang-Chi. you have nothing to fear.

1301
01:22:26.609 --> 01:22:28.820
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

1302
01:22:48.256 --> 01:22:50.258
(TRADITIONAL MUSIC PLAYING)

1303
01:22:59.517 --> 01:23:00.893
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1304
01:23:01.602 --> 01:23:03.604
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1305
01:23:11.821 --> 01:23:13.114
(INHALES DEEPLY)

1306
01:23:13.906 --> 01:23:14.991
(GASPING)

1307
01:23:15.074 --> 01:23:17.410
- (GANG MEMBERS SHOUTING)
- (BLOWS LANDING)

1308
01:23:17.493 --> 01:23:19.203
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

1309
01:23:30.756 --> 01:23:32.758
(SOMBRE MUSIC PLAYING)

1310
01:23:37.805 --> 01:23:39.015
YOUNG SHANG-CHI: Mama.

1311
01:23:41.642 --> 01:23:42.810
Mama.

1312
01:23:47.732 --> 01:23:49.150
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

1313
01:23:49.942 --> 01:23:51.068
(GASPS QUIETLY)

1314
01:23:53.654 --> 01:23:55.489
(YOUNG XIALING
SOBBING QUIETLY)

1315
01:24:01.329 --> 01:24:02.538
Papa.

1316
01:24:11.839 --> 01:24:14.884
She told me I could change.

1317
01:24:16.385 --> 01:24:19.639
That I could leave my past behind.

1318
01:24:19.722 --> 01:24:20.806
(SIGHS)

1319
01:24:22.058 --> 01:24:24.560
But she was wrong.

1320
01:24:27.772 --> 01:24:30.399
If I hadn't taken them off.

1321
01:24:31.317 --> 01:24:35.279
those men wouldn't have
dared to do this.

1322
01:24:37.740 --> 01:24:40.493
And now they will pay for it.

1323
01:24:40.576 --> 01:24:43.412
- (LOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)
- (INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

1324
01:25:11.274 --> 01:25:13.192
- (WENWU YELLING)
- (PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1325
01:25:16.195 --> 01:25:17.822
- (GUNSHOTS)
- (RINGS CLANGING)

1326
01:25:27.081 --> 01:25:28.249
(GRUNTS)

1327
01:25:28.332 --> 01:25:29.333
(GROANS)

1328
01:25:33.587 --> 01:25:34.672
(GASPS)

1329
01:25:34.922 --> 01:25:35.965
Where's your boss?

1330
01:25:36.424 --> 01:25:37.425
I don't know!

1331
01:25:37.842 --> 01:25:39.427
I swear I don't!

1332
01:25:39.802 --> 01:25:40.928
(MAN BREATHING SHAKILY)

1333
01:25:41.012 --> 01:25:42.596
Okay.

1334
01:25:44.056 --> 01:25:45.308
- (FIRES)
- (PEOPLE SCREAM)

1335
01:25:47.226 --> 01:25:48.769
(BREATHING NERVOUSLY)

1336
01:25:55.943 --> 01:26:00.698
A blood debt has to be
paid by blood.

1337
01:26:01.532 --> 01:26:03.326
Will you help me?

1338
01:26:17.214 --> 01:26:19.300
(SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1339
01:26:33.272 --> 01:26:34.482
(IN ENGLISH) We found the man

1340
01:26:34.565 --> 01:26:36.650
responsible for killing
your mother.

1341
01:26:37.860 --> 01:26:40.946
It is your right
to finish this for both of us.

1342
01:26:42.073 --> 01:26:43.699
And when you return.

1343
01:26:43.866 --> 01:26:47.370
we will rebuild The Ten Rings
to what it once was.

1344
01:27:08.891 --> 01:27:10.518
Been looking
everywhere for ya.

1345
01:27:18.442 --> 01:27:19.652
You okay?

1346
01:27:24.031 --> 01:27:27.410
I'm not who you think I am.

1347
01:27:27.576 --> 01:27:29.412
You already apologised
for that. We're good...

1348
01:27:29.578 --> 01:27:31.539
That's not what
I'm talking about.

1349
01:27:33.833 --> 01:27:35.042
Okay.

1350
01:27:36.627 --> 01:27:38.421
What... What is it?

1351
01:27:40.381 --> 01:27:41.465
(SIGHS)

1352
01:27:44.009 --> 01:27:48.848
When my dad sent me to find
the man who killed my mom...

1353
01:27:51.559 --> 01:27:53.769
I told you
I couldn't go through with it.

1354
01:27:58.816 --> 01:28:00.317
I lied.

1355
01:28:04.572 --> 01:28:06.866
I thought that
I could change my name.

1356
01:28:07.032 --> 01:28:09.952
start a new life. pretend like
it never happened.

1357
01:28:10.119 --> 01:28:11.328
But...

1358
01:28:15.791 --> 01:28:16.917
(SIGHS)

1359
01:28:18.252 --> 01:28:20.504
She would hate
the person I've become.

1360
01:28:27.219 --> 01:28:29.430
Your dad trained you
to be an assassin

1361
01:28:29.513 --> 01:28:31.432
when you were seven.

1362
01:28:32.183 --> 01:28:35.769
He sent you on a hit at 14.

1363
01:28:37.730 --> 01:28:40.107
You realise how messed up
that is. right?

1364
01:28:43.736 --> 01:28:46.238
My mom is dead because of him.

1365
01:28:49.200 --> 01:28:51.952
And now he's coming
to destroy her home.

1366
01:29:01.337 --> 01:29:04.590
(IN MANDARIN) A blood debt
has to be paid by blood.

1367
01:29:07.510 --> 01:29:09.261
(IN ENGLISH)
What are you saying?

1368
01:29:12.806 --> 01:29:15.017
I'm gonna do
what he trained me to do.

1369
01:29:21.023 --> 01:29:22.566
I'm gonna kill him.

1370
01:29:22.650 --> 01:29:24.902
(LOW SOMBRE MUSIC PLAYING)

1371
01:29:34.119 --> 01:29:36.038
(SNIFFLING)

1372
01:29:49.927 --> 01:29:51.679
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1373
01:29:58.727 --> 01:30:00.145
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1374
01:30:00.229 --> 01:30:01.855
- (GRUNTS)
- (CREATURE GRUNTS)

1375
01:30:05.025 --> 01:30:06.443
(HURRIED CHATTER)

1376
01:30:10.030 --> 01:30:11.031
He's here.

1377
01:30:17.288 --> 01:30:18.831
(ALARMED CHATTER)

1378
01:30:22.084 --> 01:30:23.085
(GUANG BO SPEAKING MANDARIN)

1379
01:30:23.377 --> 01:30:24.378
No!

1380
01:30:24.461 --> 01:30:25.713
You're not ready.

1381
01:30:25.879 --> 01:30:27.923
She stays here.

1382
01:30:28.841 --> 01:30:31.051
(DRAMATIC MUSIC SWELLS)

1383
01:30:57.244 --> 01:30:59.246
(DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES)

1384
01:31:09.214 --> 01:31:10.799
(CREATURE GROWLS)

1385
01:31:21.644 --> 01:31:23.228
(IN ENGLISH) Are you here
to help the people

1386
01:31:23.312 --> 01:31:25.773
holding your own mother
captive?

1387
01:31:26.190 --> 01:31:27.775
YING NAN:
She isn't back there.

1388
01:31:28.150 --> 01:31:29.151
You're being lied to

1389
01:31:29.234 --> 01:31:31.403
by a creature
who wants to destroy us all.

1390
01:31:32.863 --> 01:31:34.948
Is that what they told you?

1391
01:31:35.532 --> 01:31:38.160
I know my wife's voice.

1392
01:31:38.369 --> 01:31:40.913
I miss my sister
as much as you do.

1393
01:31:41.080 --> 01:31:43.666
but this is not the way
to honour her memory.

1394
01:31:43.832 --> 01:31:45.626
Did you honour her
when you turned her away

1395
01:31:45.709 --> 01:31:46.710
from your gate?

1396
01:31:46.835 --> 01:31:49.338
(IN MANDARIN)
You fool. We turned you away.

1397
01:31:49.505 --> 01:31:52.049
The sins of your past would have
destroyed this place.

1398
01:31:52.383 --> 01:31:56.679
Be careful how you speak to me.
young man.

1399
01:31:57.096 --> 01:32:00.891
I've lived ten of your lifetimes.

1400
01:32:02.434 --> 01:32:04.061
(IN ENGLISH) Let me pass.

1401
01:32:04.395 --> 01:32:06.438
We cannot do that.

1402
01:32:09.233 --> 01:32:10.234
(ALL GRUNT)

1403
01:32:13.112 --> 01:32:14.738
(RINGS HUM)

1404
01:32:16.990 --> 01:32:18.492
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1405
01:32:19.952 --> 01:32:20.953
(SIGHS)

1406
01:32:25.416 --> 01:32:26.583
Burn it down.

1407
01:32:28.752 --> 01:32:30.212
(ALL GRUNTING)

1408
01:32:30.295 --> 01:32:31.922
(GROANING)

1409
01:32:33.382 --> 01:32:35.718
- (COMMANDS IN MANDARIN)
- (FIGHTERS YELLING)

1410
01:32:47.062 --> 01:32:48.188
(FIGHTER GRUNTS)

1411
01:32:48.272 --> 01:32:50.274
- (SNARLS)
- (FIGHTER SCREAMING)

1412
01:32:50.357 --> 01:32:51.984
(ALL GRUNTING)

1413
01:32:54.945 --> 01:32:56.029
(FIGHTER YELPS)

1414
01:33:11.378 --> 01:33:12.463
(GRUNTS LOUDLY)

1415
01:33:30.522 --> 01:33:31.648
Stop him!

1416
01:33:36.737 --> 01:33:38.739
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1417
01:33:56.590 --> 01:33:58.467
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1418
01:34:07.267 --> 01:34:10.270
Are you planning to stop me
all by yourself?

1419
01:34:14.608 --> 01:34:16.026
I'm not afraid of you.

1420
01:34:23.325 --> 01:34:24.535
Yes. you are.

1421
01:34:25.244 --> 01:34:26.328
(BOTH GRUNT)

1422
01:34:30.165 --> 01:34:33.585
You've spent
your entire life afraid.

1423
01:34:33.752 --> 01:34:35.796
Always running.

1424
01:34:35.963 --> 01:34:37.256
always hiding.

1425
01:34:37.840 --> 01:34:38.841
(GRUNTS)

1426
01:34:39.925 --> 01:34:41.510
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1427
01:34:52.479 --> 01:34:54.648
You were there
when they came for her.

1428
01:34:54.815 --> 01:34:56.984
and you did nothing.

1429
01:34:57.568 --> 01:35:00.445
You stood at a window
and watched her die!

1430
01:35:04.616 --> 01:35:06.076
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

1431
01:35:08.620 --> 01:35:09.830
(SHANG-CHI GRUNTS)

1432
01:35:11.248 --> 01:35:12.833
(GRUNTING)

1433
01:35:17.170 --> 01:35:18.922
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1434
01:35:35.272 --> 01:35:36.982
She was gone
and we needed you.

1435
01:35:38.191 --> 01:35:41.403
But you chose those damn rings
over us. (SNIFFLES)

1436
01:35:41.486 --> 01:35:43.071
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1437
01:35:45.490 --> 01:35:46.992
You trained your son
to be a killer.

1438
01:35:48.201 --> 01:35:49.328
Is this what you wanted?

1439
01:35:49.828 --> 01:35:51.455
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1440
01:35:59.713 --> 01:36:01.131
(PANTING)

1441
01:36:06.720 --> 01:36:08.388
Even if you could
bring her back.

1442
01:36:10.182 --> 01:36:12.809
what makes you think she'd
want anything to do with you?

1443
01:36:15.896 --> 01:36:17.147
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1444
01:36:28.575 --> 01:36:30.118
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1445
01:36:38.418 --> 01:36:40.128
LI: (IN MANDARIN) Save me.

1446
01:36:41.129 --> 01:36:43.465
Save me. my dear.

1447
01:36:49.388 --> 01:36:50.514
(GRUNTS)

1448
01:36:54.768 --> 01:36:56.770
(SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1449
01:37:03.276 --> 01:37:05.153
Save me.

1450
01:37:05.612 --> 01:37:08.031
I'm coming. my love.

1451
01:37:11.785 --> 01:37:13.286
(GRUNTING)

1452
01:37:13.704 --> 01:37:14.913
(RATTLING)

1453
01:37:18.083 --> 01:37:19.084
(GRUNTS)

1454
01:37:19.626 --> 01:37:21.169
(RATTLING)

1455
01:37:27.759 --> 01:37:29.136
(SCREECHING)

1456
01:37:32.681 --> 01:37:34.307
- (WENWU PUNCHES)
- (RATTLING)

1457
01:37:34.391 --> 01:37:35.809
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1458
01:37:38.395 --> 01:37:39.771
(ALL GRUNTING)

1459
01:37:43.942 --> 01:37:45.694
(DISTANT SCREECHING)

1460
01:37:45.777 --> 01:37:46.903
(GASPS)

1461
01:37:46.987 --> 01:37:48.655
(SCREECHING)

1462
01:37:49.614 --> 01:37:50.824
(IN ENGLISH)
He breached the gate!

1463
01:37:55.287 --> 01:37:56.496
Those things
are gonna kill us all

1464
01:37:56.580 --> 01:37:58.165
if we don't work together.

1465
01:37:58.331 --> 01:38:00.375
You think
I'm going to fall for that?

1466
01:38:00.542 --> 01:38:02.711
Your weapons are useless
against them.

1467
01:38:03.170 --> 01:38:04.796
We don't need your help.

1468
01:38:05.338 --> 01:38:07.591
We are the mighty Ten Rings.

1469
01:38:07.674 --> 01:38:09.092
- and any...
- (CREATURE SCREECHES)

1470
01:38:17.184 --> 01:38:19.186
- (SCREECHING)
- (GRUNTING)

1471
01:38:24.232 --> 01:38:25.233
(SCREECHES)

1472
01:38:25.776 --> 01:38:27.152
(PANTING)

1473
01:38:33.784 --> 01:38:36.369
We... We should work together.

1474
01:38:36.536 --> 01:38:38.580
Release them.

1475
01:38:38.747 --> 01:38:40.499
Release them!

1476
01:38:46.254 --> 01:38:47.547
XIALING: What are they doing?

1477
01:38:47.714 --> 01:38:50.175
YING NAN: Stealing souls to
feed the Dweller-in-Darkness.

1478
01:38:50.300 --> 01:38:51.676
If it grows strong enough.

1479
01:38:51.760 --> 01:38:53.178
it will break
right through the gate.

1480
01:38:53.345 --> 01:38:55.305
That was just the beginning.

1481
01:38:55.388 --> 01:38:57.057
(URGENT CHATTER)

1482
01:38:58.225 --> 01:38:59.518
(IN MANDARIN) It's too dangerous.

1483
01:38:59.684 --> 01:39:00.936
(IN ENGLISH)
I have to help my friends.

1484
01:39:05.232 --> 01:39:07.234
(IN MANDARIN) Don't die.

1485
01:39:08.318 --> 01:39:11.071
Everyone to the water now!

1486
01:39:11.154 --> 01:39:12.364
RAZOR FIST: (IN ENGLISH)
To the lake! Let's go!

1487
01:39:12.447 --> 01:39:13.657
Let's go!

1488
01:39:15.784 --> 01:39:17.828
Hey. where's your brother?

1489
01:39:17.994 --> 01:39:19.704
I was hoping you knew.

1490
01:39:27.587 --> 01:39:28.588
LI: (IN MANDARIN) Save me.

1491
01:39:29.881 --> 01:39:30.882
(GRUNTS)

1492
01:39:30.966 --> 01:39:33.218
- (RATTLING)
- (CREATURES SCREECHING)

1493
01:39:35.470 --> 01:39:37.472
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1494
01:39:41.935 --> 01:39:43.311
(CREATURE GROWLING)

1495
01:39:49.192 --> 01:39:50.610
(SCREECHING)

1496
01:39:53.155 --> 01:39:56.074
Aim at the sky.
to win or die!

1497
01:39:59.244 --> 01:40:00.996
(SIGHING)

1498
01:40:05.959 --> 01:40:07.460
(CREATURE GROWLS)

1499
01:40:09.838 --> 01:40:11.590
Deep breath.

1500
01:40:14.718 --> 01:40:15.927
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

1501
01:40:18.346 --> 01:40:19.681
(SCREECHING CONTINUES)

1502
01:40:27.272 --> 01:40:29.733
LI: Shang-Chi. you have nothing to fear.

1503
01:40:30.901 --> 01:40:33.069
You have the heart
of our dragon.

1504
01:40:33.862 --> 01:40:37.199
I will always be a part of you.
And your dad will too.

1505
01:40:37.824 --> 01:40:41.953
Take everything we've given you
and make it your own.

1506
01:40:42.037 --> 01:40:44.039
(GENTLE STRING MUSIC PLAYING)

1507
01:40:59.221 --> 01:41:01.473
I'm so proud of you.

1508
01:41:05.810 --> 01:41:08.230
Our family needs you.

1509
01:41:09.648 --> 01:41:10.649
Go.

1510
01:41:10.732 --> 01:41:11.775
(GASPS)

1511
01:41:18.865 --> 01:41:20.909
(MUSIC RISING)

1512
01:41:49.312 --> 01:41:51.481
(INSPIRATIONAL MUSIC PLAYING)

1513
01:41:59.698 --> 01:42:00.699
(GASPS)

1514
01:42:02.575 --> 01:42:04.703
(CREATURES SCREECHING)

1515
01:42:04.786 --> 01:42:06.538
Draw.

1516
01:42:10.500 --> 01:42:11.835
Fire!

1517
01:42:13.169 --> 01:42:14.671
(FRANTIC SCREECHING)

1518
01:42:14.754 --> 01:42:16.798
(ALL GRUNTING)

1519
01:42:26.641 --> 01:42:28.310
(FRANTIC GRUNTING AND YELLING)

1520
01:42:34.149 --> 01:42:35.525
(ROARS)

